This thing is one of the best sounding cabs I've played on.  It's got clarity in spades and incredible low end -- which is lacking on most guitar cabs, bell chime sparkly highs, and tight mids.  Well balanced sound.  I've played bass through it as well and it performs like a champ.  Included is an Auralex isolation pad which fits the cab perfectly and helps to decouple it from the floor.  Cab also has removable feet, carrying handle, and removable inner insolation which helps to focus the low end in an oh so pleasing way.

description:
Carl Martin Delayla XL Pedal

Carl Martin DeLayla XL

The Carl Martin DeLayla XL is designed and developed with one goal in mind: To create a superior echo pedal, with the same sonic quality as the original DeLayla but with new extended features, yet incorporating some of the same features used in vintage tape delay units. To achieve this, they incorporated a second delay head (slapback) (similar to using two heads simultaneously on a tape delay). The SLAPBACK footswitch is used to turn the second delay head on or off. The SLAPBACK knob controls the mix of main delay vs. second delay head. Clockwise movement favors the second delay head; Counter clockwise favors the main delay. The SB-TRIM knob fine tune the second delay head's time setting compared to the original delay head, by this it's possible to create different delay patterns, going from strict slapback to way offbeat.

The TEMPO tap is a real time tempo learn function, allowing you to foot tap the delay time to match the exact beat of the song. The Carl Martin DeLayla XL also features a built in regulated power supply. The result is a warm, smooth sound reminiscent of the vintage tape units used in the 50's and 60's, combined with modern features. The Carl Martin DeLayla XL is able to capture one of the hardest sounds: That authentic rock'n roll slapback echo, that digital processors are unable to emulate.

Features:

Analog Delay plus the hard to recreate "Slapback" effect
Second Delay Tap similar to using two heads simultaneously on a tape delay
Tap Mix Knob lets you balance it just right
Built in regulated power supply
Hand Made in Denmark

contact: by email cvasquez845_gmail.com

Feel free to come on over, plug in and play this 40 watt tube powered Line 6 Bogner amp any time

For anything from bedroom studio tone to crushing live venue stage volume, this amp is IT and more

All of the amp models from the famous POD plus, this MKII especially has some truly wonderful sounds

A true modelling amp classic mated with Reinhold Bogner's infamous tube amp designing capability

Many compare to the Bogner Alchemist, though this Line 6 Bogner Valve MKII really has more sounds

Excellent condition and a very, VERY loud 40 Watts, enough for any stage or to drive a 4 X 12 cabinet

Plenty of reviews on-line and many people just never let go of these amps, which are very dependable

Tubes (valves) are in excellent working condition, and so is the original Celestion Vintage 30 speaker

"Spider Valve MkII amplifiers are the result of a groundbreaking collaboration between Line 6 and Reinhold Bogner. Boutique-style amp designs combine with the most advanced Line 6 amp modeling to deliver muscular tube tone and unsurpassed sonic flexibility. The amp and effect modeling flows into the Bogner-designed 12AX7 preamp and 6L6 power amp, and the result is a guitar-playing experience unlike any other."

Modeling upstarts meet the tube guru.

In 2007, Line 6 approached Reinhold Bogner with a radical idea. We wanted the tube-amp legend to lend his world-renowned expertise, experience and imagination on a revolutionary new series of guitar amplifiers. After careful consideration he remarked, "This opens up a world of possibilities ... let's see what we can do with it!"

More info on just the basic amp models (can be tweaked and added to considerably);

AMP MODELS


Clean Amber	One of the best-feeling clean tones we've ever made, Clean Amber is highly responsive to the player's touch. Scooped and boasting a beautiful high-end shimmer, it's inspired by* the clean tones of a Marshall® JCM-900.	


Clean Blue	Inspired by* some aspects of a Hiwatt® Custom 100, Clean Blue emulates the classic clean tones of the late 60s/early 70s. This model is full-bodied with a creamy mid-range and a tight low-end.	


Twang Amber	Twang Amber is inspired by* the sound of a 60s Fender® Blackface Twin Reverb® to produce a classic Nashville spank. Crank the Drive knob for some extra grit and growl!	


Twang Blue	More aggressive than Twang Amber, Twang Blue has plenty of cut, punch and attitude inspired by* a 60s Fender® Blackface Deluxe Reverb®.	


NEW! Class A Amber	Brilliant, singing tones with an addictive chime made famous by generations of Brit-rockers, Class A Amber is inspired by* a Vox® AC30 Top Boost.	


NEW! Class A Blue	Terrifically dynamic, Class A Blue offers boutique-style feel inspired by* some of our favorite amps including the Divided by 13 9/15. Sweet tones on the edge of breaking up give way to seriously throaty Overdrive when the Drive knob is cranked.	


Blues Amber	The vintage charm of Blues Amber is inspired by* the classic tones of a '50s wide panel Fender® Deluxe Reverb®.	


NEW! Blues Blue	Voiced with more attitude than Blues Amber, Blues Blue delivers a more forward mid-range for a classic rockabilly sound inspired by* the bite of a pint-sized Gretsch® 6156.	


Crunch Amber	A celebration of the tone used by numerous early metal bands, Crunch Amber was inspired by* the signature crunch of a '68 Marshall® Plexi 50-Watt.	


NEW! Crunch Blue	Crunch Blue provides a rounded off British-style distortion with a cool mid-honk and great cut. Inspired by* the killer crunch of an Orange® AD30.	


Hi Gain Amber	Hi Gain Amber is inspired by* the infamous brown sound of a '68 Marshall® Plexi 100-Watt with a Variac and jumped input channels.	


NEW! Hi Gain Blue	A modern, scooped metal sound, Hi Gain Blue is a refined distortion inspired by* the high-gain mayhem of a Diezel® Herbert.	


Metal Amber	A one-way ticket to high-gain heaven, Metal Amber is tight, punchy and inspired by* the high-gain tone of a Mesa/Boogie® Dual Rectifier®.	


Metal Blue	Metal Blue delivers high-gain aggression with supreme versatility. Sweep the Mid knob to control the character of the distortion! (Set it to minimum for fuzz pedal characteristics; set it to noon for creamy, modern high-gain tones; set it to max to conjure Class A tones.)	


Insane Amber	Dialed in for shredding, Insane Amber combines the intensity and impact of Metal Blue but it delivers more mid-range teeth for that bone-crushing grind. Inspired by* the tone of a Mesa/Boogie® Dual Rectifier® (red channel).	


Insane Blue	Insane Blue delivers an obscene helping of distortion while still retaining tonal definition and character. As much input gain distortion as possible short of a complete meltdown!;


~

description:
The Hughes & Kettner Triamp MK 1 is a complex, feature-laden amp that boasts an all-tube signal path. Sporting a 100W power section with 4 EL34's or 6L6GC's, along with 9 - count 'em - NINE 12AX7A's, spring reverb, also an optional MIDI control module, buffered FX Loop with db pad switch, H&K's Famous RED BOX DI, Line Out, selectable mains voltage, and Power Tube Failure indicator.

On the front panel, Three individual channels, each with two dedicated modes, dedicated EQ, Gain (one for each mode per amp - a total of six!) and Volume controls are topped off by a global master volume, Presence, and FX Loop Level control. Each channel's modes are switchable via push buttons on the face panel, or heavy duty footswitch.

UTILIZATION

The Triamp is a massive, heavy beast of an amp head, using only the best chassis material and components. A peek inside reveals a landscape of precision resistors, F&T and Vishay capacitors, as well as expertly laid ribbon cabling. The transformers are some of the largest I've ever seen in a 100 watt amp.

The EQ is responsive across all channels, and there is plenty of gain on tap for every need.

SOUNDS

AMP 1 is the clean channel. Mode 1 gives a very spanky, ballsy clean that can get slightly hairy with the gain turned up. Very touch responsive. About as close to a Fender clean as I've heard in a non-Fender amp. Kicking it into Mode 2 ups the gain and the low-end response, achieving a more Vox-like clean tone which overdrives quite well with a pedal. Not as bright as Mode 1.

Amp 2 is voiced for classic plexi-style tones. Mode 1 offers up a very thin, bright sound. Mode 2 ups the gain and the low-end. Great classic-rock sounds are found here, with plenty of midrange grind and fuzzy Marshall highs.

Amp 3 is voiced for high gain. This channel has a very strong, tight low-mid emphasis, which is typical of German high gain amps. Mode 1 produces a bright, tight grind that is great for chugging. Mode 2 goes all-out, adding even more gain and thunderous low-end response.

The FX Loop is great, allowing pedals to be implemented without much loss or coloring to the overall tone. The Red Box DI was useful for running a line to Front Of House and allowing the engineer to mix that signal with the signal mic'd from my speaker cabinet.

A great multi-use guitar amp. Nothing wrong with it. Haven't played in 5 years and need the space. Let me know if you have any questions.
title: Hughes & Kettner TriAmp MK1 MK 1 MKI Guitar Tube Amp

description:
1980 G&L F-100 Series I Guitar- $850
A Leo Fender original creation: 1980 G&L F-100 Series I solid body electric in excellent playing condition and very good cosmetic condition. All original except the tremolo bar (modern reproduction replacement) and missing plastic tip from pickup selector switch. Mahogany body, maple neck/board with 12" fretboard radius, medium C neck carve. Neck is dead straight, truss rod works, frets in great condition with no wear. Tremolo is phenomenal and holds tune reliably. Guitar feels and plays rock solid. Dual MFD humbuckers are hot but clear and full-range, with lots of highs and lows as well as mid thickness. Switching options allow for a variety of sounds, including a single coil mode and out of phase mode for thinner, phasey tone.
Nitro lacquer finish, perhaps over poly. Overall this guitar is very clean especially considering its age.
Includes original hard case in good condition.
Can demo in Farmingdale any Wed. Thur. Or Sunday nights.

Details:

Hercules Stands EZ Clutch Music Stand

The BS301B EZ Clutch music stand is proof that even gear as essential and basic as a music stand benefits from advancing technology. Hercules totally nails it, offering a stand with several handy features.

First off, it has a desk with an upper half that folds down when not in use, utilizing a side locking pin to keep it firmly closed. When you're ready to play, simply press the pin to open the desk back up and lock it in position with the clip on back.

Then there is the EZ Angle Roller, which is equipped with a special frictioning rubber that holds the desk at the perfect angle while also being instantly adjustable. A simple push of the Quik-N-Easy Retainer's lever up or down makes it possible for instant desk mounting and dismounting. The same is true for the EZ Clutch which lets you adjust the height of the upper tube with the same simple lever push action.

The tilting base lets the music stand angle from 90 to 75 degrees, to reach positions more suited for your needs. It's swivel legs fit around other equipment, perfect for crowded stages. Simply pull up on the locking ring for compact packing. Last, but not least, the legs have 2 peg holes for adding an optional instrument peg so you can store your instrument when not in use, or a second instrument without taking up any extra floor space.

description:
Selling a used A/DA MP-1 Guitar Preamp. My good buddy owned it for years and had it modded so it sounds much better than stock, before gifting it to me. It's extremely versatile, going from very clean to bluesy overdrive to marshall rawwwk to 80s metal scooped shredz. Plus it has a really awesome sounding chorus effect that you can program the depth/rate for each preset (or just leave it out). Also it's midi controllable so you can easily use in a live or studio setting with a foot controller.

The cosmetic issues are as follows:
- Output jack A needs to be replaced, but Output jack B works perfectly fine (only need 1 jack for mono guitar sources, but you can replace jack A for a few bucks.
- plastic knob on front panel output level missing (works perfectly fine though)
- hole drilled in front panel over clip gain indicator (really wouldn't need to worry if you're just running instrument level signals through it).
- rack rash - scratches and a tiny ding or two

To be honest I'm actually surprised at how good it sounds for a 30 year old guitar pre. Both the clean and clean tube modes sound excellent and are great pedal platforms, and the heavier overdrive modes can go from bluesy to marshally to 80s metal scooped. Each preset can be adjusted with 4 band eq (bass, mid, treble, presence), chorus (depth/rate), 2 overdrive levels (effected depending on which "voicing mode you select), a master gain (so you can set your levels to be similar volume, and voicing (clean, clean tube and distortion modes I believe). You can edit the presets to your liking or create your own. Also you can hook this up to a midi controller for changing between presets during a gig or studio session.

Selling for $250 cash.

NO SPAM NO SCAMS NO SPAMMERS NO SCAMMERS

description:
Gold Tone
Fretless M-Bass/FL25 MicroBass
Fretless Mini Bass Guitar
Active EQ and Built-In Tuner
25" String Length
Beautiful to Look at as Well as Play!

What a Bass! Only used one time for a recording session.
The Gold Tone fretless M-BASS with fret markers is a short scale bass that produces the same pitches as a standard bass instrument and is tuned in traditional bass tuning, E-A-D-G. This M-BASS is strung with Aquila proprietary strings that incorporate a great bass feel with balanced tension. The tone that this M-Bass produces is amazing and it's pure pleasure to play. Comes with a heavily padded gig bag.

The MicroBass M-Bass/FL, is a 25" short-scaled fretless acoustic/electric bass guitar that utilizes a dedicated Aquila "MicroBass" synthetic string and a piezo transducer pickup. The extended scale length greatly improves intonation over similar models and allows for an acoustic volume loud enough to enjoy without plugging into an amplifier. The sloped ergo-glide top makes this instrument extremely comfortable to hold.

The MicroBass features a built-in transducer pickup with a master volume control as well as independent bass and treble tone controls. There is also a built-in electronic tuner with mute function that will aid in quick and accurate pitch adjustments. When the tuner is engaged, the instrument output is muted. When a 1/4" instrument cable is inserted into the output jack, the tuner is automatically engaged and the instrument is muted. By pressing the tuner button, the tuner is disengaged and the bass output will be audible.

MicroBass models feature an active pickup, which means that a battery is required for the pickup to function. The battery and can be accessed in the built-in preamp on the upper bout of the instrument. The MicroBass uses a 9v battery, which can be accessed under the plastic cover on the backside of the instrument opposite the volume and tone controls. A battery is included with all new MicroBasses.

This MicroBass does include a 5-year factory warranty.

PLEASE INCLUDE YOUR PHONE # TO DISCOURAGE SCAMMERS & I WILL RETURN YOUR CALL ASAP
title: Gold Tone M-Bass25FL Fretless Mini Bass Guitar w/ gig bag

No nonsense, Electromatic hollow-body guitars are the perfect real, pure and powerful Gretsch instruments. They're your next-step Gretsch--bold, dynamic and articulate, and crafted with essential Gretsch sound, style and playability.

Like all Electromatic guitars, it delivers the fearless and electrifying authenticity that has set Gretsch apart as the quintessential rock 'n' roll guitars from the very beginning. It's the sound of honor itself--play proud.

description:
This bass is all original and in extremely good condition playing wise, with some marks of distinction, as expected for an instrument this age. I put a few hundred dollars into having this bass re-fretted and it received a set up from Retrofret. Because of this, this particular bass is one of the best players you'll come across, with an arrow-straight neck, fast/comfortable action and great intonation all the way up the neck.

It's a great vintage bass (early 60's) with unique feel and sound to it and it was my main player for a long time and with no reservations, playing all types of music while touring US and overseas, television performances, etc, and has even shared the stage with David Byrne (who apparently dug it and asked why I brought a different bass to the next performance). The semi-hollow body makes it very light yet these basses are known for their deep bass and clear highs. 

One of my favorites but have to sell it and hoping it goes to a good home!

*Here's a couple of live clips you can see see/hear it in:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2z0Zcbb0DDw

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MzY178Oe-nY

The record, Eli Paperboy Reed's "My Way Home" was recorded entirely with this bass straight to tape and no studio tricks, so it's a good gauge of the sound if you can stream it.

Product Information
Made In The USA
This Gibson J-100 Xtra Acoustic/Electric Guitar From 2004 is part of the guitar maker's Gibson Super Jumbo family. The J-100 Xtra engineering is also inspired by the classic SJ-100 that was a favorite of artists in the 1930s. These models are designed with larger bodies to produce a greater range of sound. This six-string machine features a solid and scalloped-braced Sitka spruce top and bubinga on the back and sides. This combination delivers an impressive and warm midrange response as well as a thundering bottom. The Gibson J-100 Xtra comes with a Fishman transducer, promising excellent acoustic amplification. It has an antique natural finish, a maple wood round neck and mustache, and a fingerboard constructed from Indian rosewood. Used by everyone from the Beatles to Led Zeppelin and Cream, the Gibson is a classic machine that delivers folk, country, hard rock, and blues.

description:
I'm selling a classic 1965 D-18 acoustic guitar. As the little brother of the D-28, it has a tonal range and presence all its own, delivering the best that a square shouldered dreadnought has to offer. 

With a solid spruce top, solid mahogany back and sides and a Brazilian Rosewood fretboard and it is thought to have a somewhat crisper sound with more definition in the top-end. The D18 model was a favorite of David Crosby and Elvis Presley. 

Light as a feather but puts out some of the most incredible sound. Lots of resonant bottom end and sharp clear high notes. Great guitar to add to any collection you may have. The guitar is very dynamic, responding to your lightest picking and more authoritative strums without losing definition.

Cosmetically, the guitar has some scratches and finish checks as seen in the photos. With time this guitar will only increase in price.

Included is a Fishman Rare Earth Magnetic Soundhole Mic Pickup system, which sells for $289 at Sweetwater Sound and hard shell case. Phone calls only please. Call Adam  show contact info

description:
Tascam CD-GT1MKII Portable Guitar Trainer and Amp

Nail the toughest licks at your own pace!

The TASCAM CD-GT1mkII Portable CD Guitar Trainer is the ultimate training and jamming tool for guitarists, vocalists, and other musicians. Take any favorite CD, plug your guitar directly into the CD-GT1's 1/4" input, put on some headphones, set the volume, and start rocking! Vocalists can do the same with a mic. 

The Slow Speed Audition feature lets you learn licks note-for-note by slowing down the CD up to 50% without changing the pitch. You can also increase the tempo in steps until you match the original performance. Added features include a guitar-cancelling function, built-in metronome, and oscillators for tuning, and split monitoring.

Advanced players can use the CD-GT1's pitch and speed controls to audition various keys and tempi for CDs they've burned of their own music. 

The CD-GT1 has 57 great-sounding, customizable effects including distortion, delay, chorus, and more. There's also a nice selection of vocal reverbs and processed sounds so you can sing along with rockers, hip-hoppers, divas, and everything in-between! 

You can set seamless in-out loop points with the CD-GT1 so that it plays the same passage over and over again so you can nail phrases. Use the footswitch input to start playing the CD from any designated point or to scroll through effects. 

You can listen on headphones, or use its line output to plug in speakers. The CD-GT1 even provides a chromatic tuner and operates on batteries to take your show on the road. Optional AC power supply. (See accessory box on this page.)

description:
Meticulous craftsmanship, extremely versatile play-ability.

This rare Vox Virage DC sounds and plays like a dream. See specs below and email or text with any questions.  Priced for a quick sale.  Good Luck.

The Virage DC is a solid wood semi-hollowbody guitar that features Integral Tonebar construction that keeps feedback at bay and yields the warm, singing resonance of a semi-hollow instrument with the focused attack of a solidbody. A custom, hand-carved neck joint with an inverse heel offers greatly enhanced upper fret access and comfort in the highest registers.

Innovative features include an ergonomically curved bodies, contoured both along its length and across its width. This unique curvature hugs close to the player, and, when combined with the guitars' slightly smaller than typical body size and their arched-top profile, affords a comfortable right arm playing position unlike previous semi-hollow offerings, as well as overall unprecedented playing comfort. The result is a guitar that fits perfectly whether the guitarist is sitting or standing.

The Virage DC employs the proprietary VOX Three-90 Pickup System, which relies on two triple-coil pickups to deliver clean, crunch and lead tones, similar to having single coil, P-90 and humbucking-style versatility all in one instrument. Its analog circuitry requires no batteries or active electronics, and provides hum free operation regardless of the tone selected. This pickup system was designed and built in the USA exclusively for VOX by DiMarzio. A three-way toggle makes selecting pickups quick and easy. Users can jump between clean, crunch and lead modes independently for each pickup with a quick flick of each pickup's 3-way mode switch.

The specially designed VOX Full Contact aluminum bridge provides thick, rich tone with clear harmonics. Extended saddle travel ensures perfect intonation for any gauge string. String loading from the back edge of the bridge enables quick and effortless string changes.

FEATURES
Hand-selected tonewoods
Neck - Mahogany
Neck Joint " Hand-Carved Inverse Heel
Body - Solid carved mahogany
Fingerboard - Bound rosewood
Inlay - Mother of Pearl
Finish - Acrylic lacquer
Nut - Bone
Fingerboard Radius - 11.8"
Width at nut - 1.7"

description:
~ 

Am often on the Upper East Side of Manhattan weekly for rehearsals if this helps (just ask)
Can meet anywhere along Rte 84 from Danbury to Fishkill / Newburgh Beacon Bridge
Occasionally in Ulster County near Kingston, Woodstock, or New Paltz for work


If YOU are READING this ad, then it is STILL available, right NOW, no need to ask... ;-) 




 Bought this and then before it arrived found a vintage tube amp that I wanted locally
  So here is a brand new amp that I want to sell in order to finance my other project

 Make me an offer or open to possible trade / trades for music, pro audio, recording gear, or ?

They are out of production, probably could not manufacture / hand wire and make a profit

Company is USA based, run by Veterans, Spec Ops, Mako 18 Watt High Gain Head

Still in original box, just as it came to me delivered here, I paid $350, yours now for $325 bucks OBO

 Hand wired, point to point (PTP) soldered, high quality components and excellent workmanship

Can't even find a hand wired amp USED for $350 - $400, much less brand new like this one

More info;

The Mako amp was designed to be a version of the classic 18 watt high gain, classic hand wired, amp.

Consider these features:

· Large (10"), heavy duty, rubber carry handle with spring steel insert. This is larger and better padded than others and is held in with "T" nuts (not just screwed into the top of the cabinet) for high strength.

· Large, two screw, steel corners with "Lip". Sure these are more expensive than others, but the built in "lip" protects the corners better. Covered in a thick, tough powder coat.

· The amp enclosure is made in the USA using full 18mm thick PLYWOOD - No MDF!!! Plywood is more expensive and harder to work with than MDF but is much stronger... no shortcuts here.

· The amp enclosure has four large rubber feet for non-slip stability with steel inserts for strength

· The amp enclosure is covered in a tough "Elephant" tolex (except as noted) for extreme wear resistance and long lasting good looks.

· The front of the amp features a heavy gauge expanded steel insert. This insert protects the internal components of the amp but allows maximum cooling. This insert is extremely strong and lightweight. Coated in a thick powder coat.



Buried in the enclosure is the amp itself. The Mako amp was designed to re-create the classic high gain amps of the past with some very refined updates. It is still hand wired by skilled professionals making each amp unique and one of a kind.

· The chassis is manufactured from high grade 16 ga. formed steel. It is coated in a thick powder coat with PVC overlays.

· The "Rooster Head" knobs are made from a strong, heat resistant polymer. These knobs are easy to operate and easy to see (this is very important on poorly lit stages)

· Preamp Tubes: Three 12AX7 (ECC83)

· Power Tubes: Two EL84 (6BQ5)

· The Mako amp features two inputs: Normal and Lead

· The normal channel delivers crisp, sparkling sound that can be driven to "break up" by pushing the normal channel volume to overdrive the tubes.

· The lead channel can produce clean and the ultimate in high gain tones and anything in between. By varying the settings of the gain, volume, and master volume a huge variety of styles and modes can be produced.



The Mako also features a full set of controls:

· Lead Gain - This sets the gain structure for the Lead channel

· Normal Gain - This sets the gain structure for the Normal channel

· Lead Volume - This sets the preamp volume of the Lead channel

· Bass, Mid, Treble, Presence - EQ controls for shaping the tone

· Master Volume - Sets the overall output volume. When used in conjunction with the channel volume and gain knobs a surprising palette of sounds can be had at lower volumes.

· Power Switch - Hi = Power output set at full 18 watts, Mi = Power output set at 9 watts, Lo = Power output set to 4.5 watts (or half these values in Triode operation)



The Power switch is in the back, the standby switch (with LED) in front. This is another nod to the musicians who play live. The power is turned on at the beginning and the Standby switch is generally toggled on and off at set breaks.

The rear panel of the amp has the following features:

· "Red Box" DI - The XLR Red Box output is, in our opinion, the very best direct recording "out" available. The Red Box DI has a very precise speaker emulator for recording directly to media (computer, tape, HDD etc)

· Triode/Pentode switch - This switch can be engaged as a "power soak" for playing high-gain, powerful sounds at lower levels. It effectively cuts the output of the power tubes while retaining full power thru the preamp tubes.

· Speaker Outputs - 4 Ohm/8 Ohm/16 Ohm. Just about any variety of speaker cabinet can be accommodated.

The highest quality precision parts are used throughout for extremely low noise: 5 watt metal oxide power resistors, 600 volt polypropylene film/foil and polyester Military Specification capacitors, full military spec PC boards, and wound to spec transformers. These quality components are then HAND WIRED to the amp. This auction includes the amp itself and the power cord.

In the end we can quote features and specifications until the cows come home, but what REALLY matters is the sound. The Mako sounds amazing! It faithfully recreates the sound of vintage 18 watt high gain amps at a fraction of the price. Of course "beauty is in the ear of the beholder" and that is why we invite you to try one today!



Dimensions: 16.75" (426mm) Wide, 9" (229mm) Tall, 9" (229mm) Deep

Weight: 23.5 lbs (10.6 Kg)

SPEC-OPS-LLC is 100% Veteran owned. 

~

description:
This is a rare item designed by a top notch audio mastering engineer named Ross Nyberg.
http://nybergmastering.com/testimonials/
It follows the design sonic of a mastering room with angled and no angled surfaces. I don`t know how he did it (see pics) but the cab has the bottom of a 1-15 without the bass trap boominess. I LOVE this cab but I`m traveling light this year.
It's not really heavy as it might look ... balances well.
20 1/2 wide
12 1/2 deep
19 tall (add 3/4" for rubber feet)
weight approx. 40lbs
Weber California 80w 8ohm speaker with very low hours on it.
I bought this from a pro player who is a mix engineer who said he had maybe 5 hours on it. I`ve used it for maybe 4 gigs since I stored it in NY and I`ve been on the road all year.
I`m going to move it before March 12th so here it is.
I`ve used it for Bari Gtr and it`s incredible ...think of those Forte cabs with the side ports for dispersion.
There`s one little scuff if you look hard but it`s in great shape.
As proof that I should not unscrew stuff ..I took out the speaker to get a pic of the guts and the screwdriver rolled out of my hand and slowly rested on the cone ... you can see two small dimples that just happened but there was no impact.

This guitar was constructed in the workshop of famed Madrid luthier Felix Manzanero, but not by Felix Manzanero, rather by a highly trained luthier in the shop, and made of the finest materials. Solid cedar top - Solid Indian Rosewood back and sides - Ebony fingerboard - Bone nut and saddle. High quality gold tuners - Rosewood bridge and headstock facing - 650/52.

It is extremely clean playing - it has great articulation, crystal clear separation of notes. This is found more often on spruce than cedar. So I feel it is the best of both worlds - the warmth of cedar and the clarity of spruce. It also has great sustain.   

There are a few small dings on the top, and one tiny milky spot on the back.  Part of the rosette is darkened and slightly raised. Obviously none of this affects the sound, which is rich and Spanish.

Will meet to show the guitar in Westchester, Connecticut, or Riverdale.

$795, including a hard shell case in very good condition.

description:
The AF610ESHB is an elegant, cosmetically rich guitar with a powerful and open tone. The solid A+ Sitka spruce top generates great energy making this an exciting and responsive instrument suitable for any style of music. The Shadowburst finish on this guitar is stunning, carefully crafted to produce a mirror deep shine and sophisticated appearance. Each model is designed to get the best out of its solid top and components, and for them to work together to produce a tone and player experience, rarely found in affordable instruments.

These components include Alvarez's FST2M bracing system, a bi-level bridge, and a real bone nut and saddle. The sound is warm, open and powerful, and both the treble and bass registers are clearly present and balanced in relation to each other. These guitars feel right and are rewarding to play.

The AF610ESHB also comes with the Alvarez SYS250 EQ and pickup system, which comes with a 3-band EQ and a backlit chromatic digital tuner to ensure you sound great when you've plugged this sweet guitar up to an amp.

Guitar is in excellent condition and is immediately playable, comes with Alvarez FC1 Folk Arched Acoustic Guitar Hardshell Case in excellent condition.

description:
Welcome. This is the Mark Sound Custom Stratocaster Electric Guitar. 25.5" scale length. 1.63" nut width. 9 lbs 8 oz.  
This beauty is based on the Custom Shop Strat. Mark Sound makes some gorgeous pieces, and this one is a prime example. The body here is northern ash which gives it a fantastic 'Les Paul' midrange push. The perfect complement to the Fender pickups.
A trio of Fender USA pickups provide everything from crisp bridge sounds to warm neck cleans. Add overdrive to these beauties and they open right up with complex mids. The middle position is non RWRP, so you get classic Fender tones across the 5 way. The bridge position has the classic 'bite' with the body's mid push adding a nice touch. The neck pickup is absolutely stunning with thick syrupy sustain. Of course, you have your tight cleans and Hendrix overdrives from the '2' & '4' positions. A true tone machine.
The maple neck here has a great feel- .86" deep at the 5th fret with an oval C profile. Super comfortable while the mass adds fantastic tone transfer. Add to that the 12" fretboard radius and you have a bender's dream ax.
The look here is beautiful- orange sparkle finish, maple board, black dot inlays, and gold hardware.
This Mark Sound is in exceptional overall condition - nothing to report. The frets here are clean- setup with action just 3/32" at the 12th fret low E.
This auction includes the hardshell case in pics(fair/good condition). 
This is your chance to get your hands on a fantastic custom Mark Sound Strat example for the price you want. Don't pass this by.
title: Mark Sound Custom Ash Stratocaster Strat Electric Guitar

description:
This is the George Fedden Custom Acrylic Offset Strat Electric Guitar. 25.5" scale. 1.74" nut width. 9 lbs 14 oz.
The George Fedden acrylic guitars are custom made to order works of art.
This beauty features a solid red & clear acrylic body- in an 'offset Strat' design- just gorgeous.
The body here, combined with the 3/4 through bolt on neck, creates an incredible amount of natural sustain. Just huge tone, with a nice bite.
Grabbing up this tone are a trio of custom made pickups- a hum in the bridge and dual single coils.
These pickups provide exceptional clean and crunch tones.
The bridge position sounds big and warm- perfect for crunchy rhythms and searing leads.
The single coil in the neck provides some warm cleans and syrupy overdrive tones.
The way the middle pickup is wired gives this guitar a great amount of flexibility. It enganges off the p/p tone control- so you can add it to either pickup or have all 3 pickups on at the same time. Very cool.
The highly figured maple neck here has a great profile- .83" deep at the 5th fret- with a comfortable soft V profile. 
Add to that the 10" fretboard radius and you have a great player- a bender's dream.
The look is incredible- red/clear 'offset Strat' acrylic body, heavy figuring on the neck, star inlays, and chrome hardware.
This beauty is in very good overall condition- typical very light wear from normal light use and a small hairline in the wooden bridge pickup surround. 
The frets are clean- just set up with action of just over 3/32" at the 12th fret low E.
This auction includes a padded gig bag.
This is your chance to get your hands on a truly amazing piece- the custom Fedden  acrylic electric guitar.
Don't pass this by!
title: George Fedden Acrylic Offset Strat Electric Guitar Highly Flamed Neck

description:
This is the Wim Heins Custom 5 String Electric Bass Guitar. 34" scale length. 1.86" nut width. 15mm string spacing at the bridge. 9.35 lbs.  Handmade to order in the Netherlands.
Wim passed away recently unfortunately, but, if you search him online, you'll see some of his other impressive builds.
As many of you are aware, we bought out NYC Bass Loft several years ago. The Bass Loft was the hang place for a number of world renowned bassists when they were in NY. The Bass Loft had all the high end luthier basses in stock. This Heins is the last piece we have from the buyout.
This bass is a handmade beauty. The body here looks to be walnut- absolutely gorgeous. This enables a warm tone with very good projection. The set maple neck adds great tone trasnfer as well as some nice high end mids.
This awesome natural tone is grabbed by the dual Bartolini J style pickups. These run into the 9v 2 band active EQ- Treble/Bass with an acitve/passive P/P off the volume. This puts a world of tones right at your fingertips. 
The set neck here is super thin- just .77" deep at the 5th fret with a flat C profile. Super comfortable while the deep body cutaways and set design enable full access all the way to the 25th fret.
The look here is beautiful- the satin finish lets the wood grains really shine. Add to that the black hardware, 3+2 headstock, and large dot inlays and you have a work of art.
This Heins is in very good overall condition - there are some surface marks, finger-rooting compressions,near the bridge pickup and scratches from normal use, but nothing that affects the performance. The frets here are clean- setup with action just over 3/32" at the 12th fret low E.
This auction includes the hardshell case in pics. This has a band name painted on the outside, in fair condition, but does the job. 
This is your chance to get your hands on a fantastic custom luthier example for the price you want. Don't pass this by.
title: Wim Heins Custom Luthier 5 String Electric Bass Guitar NYC Bass Loft

description:
This is the Vintage 1963 Gibson USA Les Paul SG Electric Guitar. 24.75" scale. 1.69" nut width. 6 lbs 14 oz. Serial #: 116XXX. Pots dated to 1962. Unbroken original solder.
This is a very exciting piece- you don't see many left handed '63 SG's. This one is the result of a custom order from Gibson.
This beauty has everything you could want from a vintage Gibson- incredible light weight, and naturally aged woods, resulting in incredible natural resonance. 
Dual Gibson humbucker pickups grab this natural tone and add in their famous classic mids.
Both pickups meter in the 7.6k area.
The PAF bridge pickup lives up to its name- almost 3 dimensional in its midrange. A spectacular outing.
The Pat No Sticker neck pickup provides excellent syrupy sustain while retaining note definition.
A beautifully matched pickup pair creating a true tone machine.
The neck here has a comfortable feel- .89" deep at the 5th fret with a C profile.
The look here is classic- natural finish, Bigsby trem, bound fingerboard, trapezoid inlays, inlaid Crown & logo, Les Paul truss cover, and chrome hardware. 
This '63 SG is in good overall condition- old heel repair, bridge post moved at some point(pic), missing Bigsby arm, and the typical marks you expect but nothing that affects the performance whatsoever.
The original bridge pickup ring was replaced(cracked) but is included in the case.
The frets here are clean- set up with action of 3/32" at the 12th fret low E. 
This auction includes the original hardshell case in pics. 
This is your chance to get your hands on a great rare vintage Gibson for the price you want. 
***FEEL FREE TO MAKE AN OFFER***

description:
Pick up only. Cash only.

Great beginner guitar and amp with everything you need to get started, awesome value, can't find this new anywhere in stores or online. Hardly used, almost pristine condition. Looking for a loving home for this set, perhaps for a rockstar in the making. Fun fact, amp doubles as an iPod speaker.

Laguna Ultimate Rock Rack Electric Guitar Pack with Spider III 15W Amp 3-Tone Sunburst

OVERVIEW
A rock-ready guitar plus modeling combo amp complete with all the extras for an unbelievable price!

Laguna and Line 6 have combined forces to produce the ultimate package for players looking for great rock tones. This ultimate rock pack includes the Laguna LE122 electric guitar, the Line 6 Spider III 15 modeling combo amplifier, and an extremely well-stocked accessory kit.

Laguna LE122 Electric Guitar
A high quality, feature rich, solid premium wood guitar with a comfort carved top. The maple neck is fast and comfortable and has a thick Indian rosewood fingerboard with offset markers for easy visibility. Uniquely wound humbuckers produce massive gain and feature a 3-position pickup switch. A traditional tremolo adds dive-bombing excitement to your solos.

Line 6 Spider III 15 Modeling Combo Amplifier
The Line 6 Spider III 15 Modeling Combo Amplifier delivers detailed amp models based on some of the greatest guitar sounds ever created. To keep these sounds authentic, Line 6 kidnapped some of the world's most notorious rock stars to dial in each amp model, including 311, Thursday, Lacuna Coil, Hawthorne Heights, Slipknot, Ash, Albert Lee, Athlete, John 5, and many more! Now you can rule the stage with the Insane model with its truly massive gain or explore your sensitive side in the studio with the Clean model. It's all up to you.

Amp Models:
Clean: Red LED - Select this Amp Model and adjust the tone controls to get crisp, amazing clean sounds, great warm jazz tones, and all the high-end shimmer you'll need with a generous amount of bottom end.

Crunch: Red LED - This sound was crafted during Line 6's studies* of the '68 Marshall Plexi 50 Watt. This type of Marshall amp was used by a number of early metal bands. Crunch provides a wider range of tone control settings than the original Marshall amp had.

Metal: Red LED - This Amp Model is based on* the Mesa/Boogie Dual Rectifier. Use this Amp Model to get a tight and punchy, high gain Metal sound.

Insane: Red LED - This model is Line 6's "dialed in for shredding" version based on* the Mesa/Boogie Dual Rectifier red channel. It combines the intensity and impact of Metal Red, but delivers more midrange and teeth for that bone-crushing, brain piercing insane grind.

Effects:
A great amp isn't the only part of a great guitar sound. With Smart Control FX, an exclusive Line 6 feature that automatically dials in different effect parameters, you spend more time playing and less time tweaking. Simply find the effect that you want, turn the knob to your desired intensity, and you're done. You can even use multiple effects at the same if you wanna get really crazy.

Effects Models (Up to 2 effects simultaneous)
Phaser
Chorus/Flanger
Tremolo
Sweep Echo
Tape Echo
Reverb

Ins & Outs
When you're playing with your band on stage just drag the Spider III on stage and crank it up. When it comes time to record, use the headphone/direct out and plug it straight into the mixing board for world-class POD 2.0 direct tone used in pro studios and stages everywhere! You can also use the same out with headphones for practicing in your bedroom. Want to play along with your favorite songs? Plug into the CD/MP3 input and you're good to go.

Plug in and separate yourself from the posers.

*All product names used in this webpage are trademarks of their respective owners, which are in no way associated or affiliated with Line 6. These trademarks of other manufacturers are used solely to identify the products of those manufacturers whose tones and sounds were studied during Line 6's sound model development.

Accessory kit
Nylon gig bag with 2 sturdy handles, a shoulder strap and large front pocket with hook and loop fabric closure; DVD; Diana IC-10 electronic chromatic tuner with 1/4" input, condenser mic for acoustic instruments, and multicolor LED indicator lights;
nylon weave guitar strap adjustable 26" - 46";
noiseless 10' instrument cable; adjustable, padded, dynamic headphones with 1/8" stereo plug (includes 1/4" stereo adapter); picks; extra set of strings.

LAGUNA GUITARS LAUNCHES "ONE GUITAR, ONE TREE" REFORESTATION INITIATIVE

Laguna Guitars, reflecting the passionate convictions of musicians, celebrates Earth Day by launching their new "One Guitar, One Tree" reforestation initiative. This plan involves planting one tree for every Laguna guitar made. In addition, Laguna continues to deepen its other practical efforts to reduce waste, recycle and conserve the planet's resources.

For decades, musicians have proudly been socially aware and urged others to take more action, advocacy and awareness in environmental matters. As musicians themselves, those at Laguna have always passionately supported that position, knowing that trees are an economical, long-term solution to many tough environmental problems, including air and water pollution, climate change, wildlife protection, habitat restoration and more. In partnership with AmericanForests.org and their Global Relief campaign, Laguna proudly plants a tree for each Laguna guitar made.

In addition, Laguna's shipping cartons are designed to provide maximum protection with a minimum of material. Their boxes are made from 100% recycled cardboard that is also 100% recyclable, which they naturally encourage wherever possible. Also, in the interests of conservation, they have decided not to print glossy, heavyweight catalogs as millions from various companies end up in landfills every year. Instead, Laguna provides extensive information online at their website (www.playlaguna.com) and a catalog will soon be available as downloadable PDF's, allowing users to print only those pages they want.

	•	4 User-programmable channels
	•	CD/MP3 jack
	•	Headphone/Direct Out for practice or recording
	•	Custom 8" speaker
	•	15 Watts

Accessory kit
	•	Nylon Gig bag

	•	10' instrument cable

	•	Extra set of strings

Uniquely wound humbuckers produce massive gain and feature a 3-position pickup switch. A traditional tremolo adds dive-bombing excitement to your solos.

Line 6 Spider III 15 Modeling Combo Amplifier
The Line 6 Spider III 15 Modeling Combo Amplifier delivers detailed amp models based on some of the greatest guitar sounds ever created. To keep these sounds authentic, Line 6 kidnapped some of the world's most notorious rock stars to dial in each amp model, including 311, Thursday, Lacuna Coil, Hawthorne Heights, Slipknot, Ash, Albert Lee, Athlete, John 5, and many more! Now you can rule the stage with the Insane model with its truly massive gain or explore your sensitive side in the studio with the Clean model. It's all up to you.

Amp Models:
Clean: Red LED - Select this Amp Model and adjust the tone controls to get crisp, amazing clean sounds, great warm jazz tones, and all the high-end shimmer you'll need with a generous amount of bottom end.

Crunch: Red LED - This sound was crafted during Line 6's studies* of the '68 Marshall Plexi 50 Watt. This type of Marshall amp was used by a number of early metal bands. Crunch provides a wider range of tone control settings than the original Marshall amp had.

Metal: Red LED - This Amp Model is based on* the Mesa/Boogie Dual Rectifier. Use this Amp Model to get a tight and punchy, high gain Metal sound.

Insane: Red LED - This model is Line 6's "dialed in for shredding" version based on* the Mesa/Boogie Dual Rectifier red channel. It combines the intensity and impact of Metal Red, but delivers more midrange and teeth for that bone-crushing, brain piercing insane grind.

Effects:
A great amp isn't the only part of a great guitar sound. With Smart Control FX, an exclusive Line 6 feature that automatically dials in different effect parameters, you spend more time playing and less time tweaking. Simply find the effect that you want, turn the knob to your desired intensity, and you're done. You can even use multiple effects at the same if you wanna get really crazy.

Effects Models (Up to 2 effects simultaneous)
Phaser
Chorus/Flanger
Tremolo
Sweep Echo
Tape Echo
Reverb

Ins & Outs
When you're playing with your band on stage just drag the Spider III on stage and crank it up. When it comes time to record, use the headphone/direct out and plug it straight into the mixing board for world-class POD 2.0 direct tone used in pro studios and stages everywhere! You can also use the same out with headphones for practicing in your bedroom. Want to play along with your favorite songs? Plug into the CD/MP3 input and you're good to go.

Plug in and separate yourself from the posers.

*All product names used in this webpage are trademarks of their respective owners, which are in no way associated or affiliated with Line 6. These trademarks of other manufacturers are used solely to identify the products of those manufacturers whose tones and sounds were studied during Line 6's sound model development.

Accessory kit
Nylon gig bag with 2 sturdy handles, a shoulder strap and large front pocket with hook and loop fabric closure; DVD; Diana IC-10 electronic chromatic tuner with 1/4" input, condenser mic for acoustic instruments, and multicolor LED indicator lights;
nylon weave guitar strap adjustable 26" - 46";
noiseless 10' instrument cable; adjustable, padded, dynamic headphones with 1/8" stereo plug (includes 1/4" stereo adapter); picks; extra set of strings.

LAGUNA GUITARS LAUNCHES "ONE GUITAR, ONE TREE" REFORESTATION INITIATIVE

Laguna Guitars, reflecting the passionate convictions of musicians, celebrates Earth Day by launching their new "One Guitar, One Tree" reforestation initiative. This plan involves planting one tree for every Laguna guitar made. In addition, Laguna continues to deepen its other practical efforts to reduce waste, recycle and conserve the planet's resources.

For decades, musicians have proudly been socially aware and urged others to take more action, advocacy and awareness in environmental matters. As musicians themselves, those at Laguna have always passionately supported that position, knowing that trees are an economical, long-term solution to many tough environmental problems, including air and water pollution, climate change, wildlife protection, habitat restoration and more. In partnership with AmericanForests.org and their Global Relief campaign, Laguna proudly plants a tree for each Laguna guitar made.

In addition, Laguna's shipping cartons are designed to provide maximum protection with a minimum of material. Their boxes are made from 100% recycled cardboard that is also 100% recyclable, which they naturally encourage wherever possible. Also, in the interests of conservation, they have decided not to print glossy, heavyweight catalogs as millions from various companies end up in landfills every year. Instead, Laguna provides extensive information online at their website (www.playlaguna.com) and a catalog will soon be available as downloadable PDF's, allowing users to print only those pages they want.

description:
1973-1975 Dallas Arbiter era Sound City 120. 

This one is very clean and works great. Very little 'white noise', which these can be known for due to the active eq. Speaking of the active eq, the one on this one sounds great and works great. A lot of people like to swap out the preamp for a Hiwatt-style or plexi-style but I decided to keep this one because I didn't find any reason to change. Also, you can plug in your favorite external eq into the 'slave input', which bypasses the onboard preamp and essentially turns this amp into a very powerful power amp.

I had this professionally gone over about a year ago and ended up with some new caps, 6 new JJ EL34 power tubes, and a 3-pronged cord. 

Works great as a 'clean platform' for pedals due to the huge Partridge transformers and 6 power tubes. Also has very nice gain on tap if you want.

Located in Brooklyn, NY.

I am NOT interested in trades - I need the dough.

-Brandon

description:
Serial Number: 92032023 -- The serial number indicates that this was the 23rd instrument produced on July 21, 1992, which was the very first year of the J-60's production. It features a Sitka spruce top and rosewood back and sides. The J-60 is one of Gibson Acoustic's most powerful dreadnought square shoulder designs.  Production of the J-60 ended in 1999, but was re-introduced for one year only, in 2013.

A birthday gift from my (then) wife in August of 1992, it is in "like-new" condition. Having been little played (I was never really very good), it has been sitting on the top shelf of my closet for over 20 years. The only flaw is a slight 5mm nick (as shown in photo #3). The deluxe hardshell case is in good condition BUT is without its combination lock (as shown in photo #5).

Many consider this superior guitar to be an heirloom...research the Gibson J-60 on Google and decide for yourself. Here is a YouTube link to the story of the production of the J-60 and a demo of the prototype built as a personal project of John Lowell in 1991 (followed by production in 1992): https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5-X8by4Gbjg

Additionally, there are good reviews and demos of the J-60 on YouTube: Just type "Gibson J-60" in the search bar...and do read the comments.

In 2013 the J-60 listed for $2,999.00 on Gibson's website:
http://www.gibson.com/Products/Acoustic-Instruments/Square-Shoulder/Gibson-Acoustic/J-60.aspx

Your personal examination of the instrument is welcome, but please note that the price is FIRM. The current fair market value of the J-60 is between $1700-$2300 (depending on its condition). Therefore, the price of $1500 for this 1992 original is already substantially discounted.

IF YOU ARE READING THIS LISTING THE GUITAR IS STILL AVAILABLE

Tail:	Standard tremolo

(1) Tone

Hardware Color:	Chrome

Year of First Catalog Appearance:	1983
Catalog Appearances:	1983 Ibanez Electric Guitars and Acoustic Guitars 
1983 Ibanez X-Series

Footnotes:
[1]	the Serial Number Format for this model may be either K302xxx or myypppp. For both the DT-150 and the DT-155 models, it appears that the serial numbers prior to approximately June 1983 are in the format K302xxx. We do not currently know how this format breaks down. 

For the DT-150 and the DT-155 models produced in June 1983 and later, the serial number format is myypppp where: 

m = month of manufacture (e.g.: A = Jan, B = Feb, ... , K = Nov, L = Dec) 
yy = last two digits of the year of manufacture (e.g.: 83 = 1983) 
pppp = the sequential production number for this individual guitar out of all Ibanez electric guitars manufactured during the specified month/year at a given factory 

Note: pppp is not the total number of guitars manufactured of this model.

[2]	the targeted Market values are assumptions based upon the geographic region or the language of the catalog(s) in which a given model appears. If a model appears in a Japanese language catalog, the Market is assumed to be East. If a model appears in an English language catalog, the Market is assumed to be West. Otherwise, geographic area such as North America or Asia determines the market designation of East or West.
Includes Case
Condition: USED-Good

description:
You're looking at an awesome GUITAR RESEARCH T30R TUBE Amplifier! This is for all those guitar players that want that saturated sound of authentic TUBE Amplifiers without breaking the bank! Guitar Research has put together the perfect combination of a 30w Tube amplifier with everything you need.

Comes in a sleek Red Tolex. Features 3 control EQ and also has gain, volume and overdrive. This will play beautiful cleans or scream with crunch tone! Easy to carry lightweight amplifier with handle and rubber feet. If playing any larger gig, just mic up your awesome Tube tone and you're ready to go!

In excellent condition.

These amps have RAVE reviews and are getting very hard to find!

Don't miss your chance to own this awesome amp!

To start, this combo is LOUD! The volume knob goes from 1: almost silent, to 2:jump-out-of-your-seat-with-suprise loud! It has phenominal sound quality; crystal clear and resonsive. And to think it comes out through an unheared of Korean driver is beyond me. It doesn't sound quite like any one Jensen, Celestion, or Eminence speaker I've heared before; it's VERY warm, but not particularly tube-like. It has its own tonal qualities. All three-band equalization knobs (BASS, MIDDLE,TREBLE) work very well and create a wide range tones. The amp's built-in over drive sounds slightly cheesey, but not too bad; I've heard much worse. When the overdrive button is engaged, the previously dialed-in gain essentially doubles, creating more of a distortion, rather than overdrive. The points at which the amp sounds its very warmest are: 1- when the volume is between 4 and 5 and the gain is at ten, and 2- when the volume is between 5 and 6, with the gain at 3 and the over drive engaged. I have tested these settings with both an ES-335 and a '52 reissue Telecaster and the two sound equally awesome. The reverb is great aswell. Using this combo with squeeze-boxes increases versitility of tones greatly. Oweing to the amp's size, it is terrific for rehearsal and recording applications. If you feel you must REALLY tweak the tone, replacing the speaker with a Jensen C12Q would warm up the sound quite a bit, however I think it's fine how it is.
title: Guitar Research T30R Electric Guitar TUBE AMPLIFIER Amp Quality Sound

description:
I have for sale an excellent NYC-finished 2009 Sadowsky Semi Hollow guitar in the hard-to-find antique blonde finish.  It is in excellent, like-new condition and has no issues. It has only been lightly used and played in my home.

It comes with its original HSC, also in excellent condition, as well as all its other original parts such as its truss rod wrench and stock pick guard which are stored in the case.

To the best of my knowledge from a direct contact with Roger, this is one of the last of the Semi Hollows to be finished in nitro, however if this is important to you, I suggest that you confirm it with Sadowsky Guitars. All of the newer ones are finished in poly.

I had a solid ebony pick guard custom made by the well-known Long Island luthier/guitar builder, Chris Mirabella, and you will see that in some of the pictures. It is fit to the guitar perfectly, but the idea of it is that it required NO SCREW HOLES IN THE GUITAR as the Sadowsky stock pick guard does. It's attached to the pickup surrounds and can be removed by 4 screws that come from the surrounds themselves. No extra parts, no holes, no hassle.

With the Custom pickguard, the asking price is $3400. The Custom one is the one pictured.

But the Custom pick guard is optional and in case you don't want it, you can take $150 off of my asking price which brings it down to $3250. You still get the stock Sadowsky ebony pickguard (uninstalled).

I will entertain some reasonable offers so get in touch if you want one of the best of the 335 type guitars available for any genre of music.

Thanks.
title: SADOWSKY SEMI HOLLOW (335 type) GUITAR BLONDE - Exc.

description:
Alchemist spins the visions of discerning guitarists into gold.

The Bogner Alchemist 112 combo amp is a modern take on vintage tube amp design. Boasting sparkling, articulate cleans, touch-sensitive leads and a bright and colorful crunch, the Alchemist 112 guitar amp owes its remarkable tonality to a 6L6 class-A/B power section, 5 - 12AX7 preamp tubes and a premium Celestion speaker. The Bogner Alchemist 112 amp owes its timeless appeal to classic innovation, modern ingenuity and some entrancing sonic alchemy. 

The Bogner Alchemist 112 has a 2-channel design. Each channel has its own voice and identity. Beginning clean and fast, featuring an open top-end and tight bottom-end, Channel 1 opens gradually to present simmering blues tones that churn like spirits in a cauldron. Advancing toward saturation, Crunch mode turns up the heat adding the perfect touch of nastiness with added pick response and increased tonal complexity. Channel 2, achieving critical mass, invokes the famous white-hot Bogner gain"creamy, modern and screaming with sustain"offering everything from Brit rock right through to modern metal. Plus, with variable Bright settings, each channel can be customized to match the tone of your guitar and rig.

Featuring a selectable power section, from 40 to 20 watts, the Alchemist 112 amp's sonority quickly transforms to display a very different kind of magic. When switched to 20 watts, the Bogner Alchemist 112 amp undergoes a complete sonic metamorphosis, changing its harmonic complexity and feel to conjure the essence of the legendary Brown sound.

Reverb and Delay, in variable styles and levels, run in parallel, separate from the original signal. The result is a rich, living and breathing, fully realized resonance capable of producing a complete tonal landscape. 


FEATURES
NEW 6L6 class-A/B power section and NEW 5 - 12AX7 preamp tubes; selectable power section (40 or 20 watts)
One 12" premium Celestion speaker
Channel 1 (gold): Gain, Treble, Mid, Bass, Volume, Crunch mode, variable Bright, Deep switch; Channel 2 (mercury): Gain, Treble, Mid, Bass, Volume, variable Bright, Mid Shift; Shared: in parallel, Reverb Type, Reverb Level, Delay Type, Delay Level, Delay Repeats (Feedback), Tap Tempo
Eye-catching retro-modern fit-and-finish
title: Bogner Alchemist 112 combo guitar amp!

description:
Beautiful Martin Vintage Series OM-28V for sale.  2010 model - has been well-kept (see note below) and plays beautifully.  It turns out I'm not playing this one as much as one should, so wanted to give it a good new home.  


Note - it must have gotten a little dry this winter, and as of very recently there is a small crack on the top (see in photos) - my understanding is, very common and easy to fix, doesn't affect playability or sound at all but the price reflects a discount for having to possibly make the repair.  Other than that, a couple of very tiny dings and otherwise in great shape.  Get in touch to see / test / play / buy.

Here's some more about this model:

The Martin OM28-V Vintage Reissue Acoustic Guitar has a silky sweet tone produced by a solid Sitka spruce top combined with narrow-waisted comfort and sumptuous appointments. Solid East Indian rosewood back and sides, bold herringbone top inlay, grained ivoroid binding and heel cap, HD zigzag back purfling, and a black ebony fretboard mark this one as a true luxury instrument. Traditional scalloped 1/4" bracing, solid mahogany neck, modified V neck shape, traditional open-geared Gotoh nickel tuners with butterbean knobs, and a Corian nut make the guitar authentic and ready for years of serious use. Includes case.

Features
Solid Sitka spruce top
Solid East Indian rosewood back and sides
Black ebony fretboard
Solid mahogany neck
Bold herringbone top inlay
Grained ivoroid binding and heel cap
HD zigzag back purfling
Scalloped 1/4" bracing
Modified V neck shape
Open-geared Gotoh nickel tuners
Tortoise pickguard
Corian nut

1-3/4" width at nut

16" radius white Micarta saddle
Polished gloss finish
Includes Geib Style case

Line 6/Bogner Spider Valve 112 Combo Guitar Amp
great tones, models and digital effects PLUS the warmth and power of real tubes

This is a masterful collaboration between legendary German boutique tube 
amp craftsman Reinhold Bogner and the sound-modeling scientists at Line 6!

It fuses the versatility of digital modeling with the performance and feel of a world-class tube amplifier.

The Spider Valve design combines 12AX7 preamp tubes with Line 6's signature modeling front-end, a marriage that allows each part of the sonic equation to deliver what it does best: creamy, cascading distortion and enriched harmonics from the tubes, and 12 of the world's finest amp models and seven stunning effects from the modeling front end. And, of course, perfectly matched 6L6 power tubes driving a Celestion Vintage 30 speaker to deliver unprecedented sonic impact and spatial imaging.

With the simple front-end controls and display, programmable patches and presets are instantly within reach. Tweak your tone even further with the front panel Presence, Drive, Bass, Mid and Treble controls: this is a true-blue tube amp, and it acts like one, responding and delivering all the analog detail, performance and warmth of every amp model and effect.
The Spider Valve 112 features 12 dialed in amp models (channel voices) that deliver a complete tonal range from shimmering clean to insane grind, and allows you to access 7 Smart Control FX (up to 3 simultaneously)--including Tape Echo, Sweep Echo, Standard Delay (all with Tap Tempo) Chorus/Flanger, Phaser, Tremolo and Reverb. The Spider Valve also has a built-in front-panel tuner, 36 user programable channels, over 300 artist created presets, and a POD XLR direct out for studio-direct tone.

    Twang Blue - based on* a number of vintage tweed amps. We evaluated a '53 Fender® tweed Deluxe Reverb®, '58 Fender® tweed Bassman® and a '60 Gibson® Explorer to create a swingin' Rockabilly tone.

Line 6/Bogner Spider Valve 112 Combo Guitar Amp
great tones, models and digital effects PLUS the warmth and power of real tubes

This is a masterful collaboration between legendary German boutique tube 
amp craftsman Reinhold Bogner and the sound-modeling scientists at Line 6!

It fuses the versatility of digital modeling with the performance and feel of a world-class tube amplifier.

The Spider Valve design combines 12AX7 preamp tubes with Line 6's signature modeling front-end, a marriage that allows each part of the sonic equation to deliver what it does best: creamy, cascading distortion and enriched harmonics from the tubes, and 12 of the world's finest amp models and seven stunning effects from the modeling front end. And, of course, perfectly matched 6L6 power tubes driving a Celestion Vintage 30 speaker to deliver unprecedented sonic impact and spatial imaging.

With the simple front-end controls and display, programmable patches and presets are instantly within reach. Tweak your tone even further with the front panel Presence, Drive, Bass, Mid and Treble controls: this is a true-blue tube amp, and it acts like one, responding and delivering all the analog detail, performance and warmth of every amp model and effect.
The Spider Valve 112 features 12 dialed in amp models (channel voices) that deliver a complete tonal range from shimmering clean to insane grind, and allows you to access 7 Smart Control FX (up to 3 simultaneously)--including Tape Echo, Sweep Echo, Standard Delay (all with Tap Tempo) Chorus/Flanger, Phaser, Tremolo and Reverb. The Spider Valve also has a built-in front-panel tuner, 36 user programable channels, over 300 artist created presets, and a POD XLR direct out for studio-direct tone.

description:
David Gries is a well-known builder of boutique amps - known for his excellent design and high build quality. This Gries 20 was one of his first models. This particular amp is actually #1, the first Gries 20 David built.

The 20 was David's homage to the venerable Fender Deluxe Reverb amp. With a few very sensible changes and upgrades. First, it's a one channel amp, not two. 20 watts, vs. the 22 watts of the DR. Unlike the DR, the Gries 20 has an excellent master volume, also bias test points on the back panel. It also has a truly superior reverb circuit - equal to or better sounding than the best of the Fender combo reverbs I've heard.

I'm not sure of the year. Probably 2006 or 2007. It's in excellent shape, cosmetically and electronically. There are some light marks on the cabinet. No rips or tears. Inside, it's been fitted with all NOS tubes: a pair of RCA blackplate 6v6, a Sylvania 5AR4 rectifier, Bogen, Mullard, RFT and Tesla preamp tubes. No expense was spared here ... this amp sounds wonderful!! The stock speaker was swapped for an Eminence CRex ceramic (lighter, better). Comes with a slightly oversized padded cover from leCover.

More pix here: https://imgur.com/a/0Y05v

If you appreciate a good deluxe reverb, then you will appreciate this amp. It's rare. I've never seen another one. The MV makes it quite flexible, easy to use in even low volume settings. It's just as tasty in a whole different way when you get to turn it up. Please, no trades.
title: FS: Gries 20 1x12 Guitar Amplifier
Trade Fender guitar gig bag for bass gig bag or keyboard case

About HORA Musical Instruments
Since 1951

The city of Reghin, called the city of violins, is synonymous with musical instruments production in Romania. This is because in Reghin there are many companies producing musical instruments, especially bowed ones. The most important of them is HORA. With a tradition of almost 60 years, a turnover of 5 million euros and about 300 workers, HORA is the biggest factory for bowed instruments and guitars in Europe.

HORA was founded in 1951 by the master luthier Roman Boianciuc who built the first violin in Reghin.

Now the factory produces yearly more than 50.000 guitars, 5.000 mandolins, 10.000 violins and 2.500 cellos and double basses.

In the last years, HORA has had more and more success with traditional ethnic instruments like mandolins, mandolas, Irish bouzoukis, cobzas, domras, balalaikas, hammer dulcimers, Appalachian dulcimers, psalteries, cimbaloms, panflutes. There are not many producers of such instruments at a professional standard and HORA found a good market niche for them.

The concern for the environment made HORA use more and more water based lacquers which suit even better not only the traditional instruments but also the guitars and even violins. The finish with this kind of lacquers produces open and powerful sound of the instrument.

The spruce and maple wood is from Romanian Carpathians Mountains seasoned naturally for 5-10 years. Exotic wood like mahogany, indian rosewood, ebony is also used.

HORA distributes its instruments all over the world through distributors and also by retail. 80% from the production goes to well known distributors from U.S.A., Canada, Germany, Italy, France, Spain, Sweden, Finland, Israel, Russia, Japan etc.

The musical instruments produced by HORA are quality confirmed by ISO9001 certificates and comply with the demands of a very broad spectrum of customers. They provide support to beginners, are reliable for experienced players and give inspiration to virtuosos.
title: Spanish Acoustic Guitar, 7 Strings HORA

description:
Here is a very cool and rare Danelectro guitar from 1961. 

The good:
The coolest most vibey vintage guitar you can find without taking out a second mortgage!
From what I can tell the guitar is all original including its chipboard case.
The master volume knob dates to the 38th week of 1961 and the concentric knobs I can not read well enough to date them but I believe are original. 
The guitar plays great and stays in tune well with good action and a straight neck. 
Two of the three concentric volume control knobs appear to be original and I have placed a third on their from a 90's reissue Dano. 

The not so good:
Somehow someway the logo on the headstock decided to separate from this guitar but you can still see where the finish aged around it, which is pretty cool in my opinion. I will include a replacement decal with a decal solution however if you don't find it as cool as I do.
There is a small crack in the body where the neck and the body join together but I don't think it is anything to be worried about. The case of the middle position lipstick pickup is splitting on the top half but that is easily replaced or can just be left as it has no effect on the sound. 
The guitar is also missing the "chicken head" type knobs/switches that are used to turn on and off each pick up but that can still be done with easy without them. 
The guitar also appears to have had a floating tail piece or maybe even a bigsby at some point with some speed holes drilled in near the strap button around the base of the guitar. 
The middle pick up volume knob can be kind of finicky on occasion but also is something that is fine 99% of the time. 
There are also various dings around the body that you would expect with a guitar that's 56 years old 

This is a truly fantastic and rare guitar that you can get for a fraction of what they go for in mint condition, don't let this one get away!

Let me know if you have any questions as well!
title: *DEAL!!* $900 1961 DANELECTRO DELUXE TRIPLE PICKUP

description:
For sale is my Hiwatt Lead 30 combo amp, model CS-30. It is extremely rare and in phenomenal condition for a 30+ year old Hiwatt. I just had it fully serviced and it has been given a clean bill of health from my local amp tech. Proof/documentation of work performed will be given to the buyer. The tubes are all good and the amp is stock, no modifications. All of the chicken head knobs are all original. Everything is original on the amp except for the RCA wires which go from the reverb tank to the amp. I had new RCA wires installed by the guitar tech. I still have the old RCA wires if you would like to keep them. The tolex has some scuffs here and there but nothing major, no eye sores. If you require additional pictures feel free to contact me. Sorry, not interested in any trades. The speaker is a stock 12" Celestion G12k-85.

These amps are becoming more difficult to find and when you do finally come across one it's usually beat up heavily modified or in much need of costly repairs!! This amp was distributed through Sterling Imports between 1983-1984. 

It is supposed to be a 30-watt amp but to my ears it's more like 80-100 watts.
title: HIWATT LEAD 30 COMBO NEW LOWER PRICE

description:
condition: like new 
make / manufacturer: Gibson 
model name / number: ES-5 Switchmaster 
1996 Gibson ES-5 Switchmaster Custom Shop hollow body guitar. Mint Condition. $4500 firm, cash only. Highly figured Maple back and top. Dark Rosewood fingerboard with insanely figured Mother of Pearl block inlay. 

Yes, this is the same model Frank Zappa used to record his iconic Freak Out! album as well as his two follow up albums Absolutely Free and Lumpy Gravy. 
Also the sound Steve Howe of Yes chose when he recorded "I've seen all good people". The Gibson ES-5 is a legendary three pickup electric archtop guitar that was made from June 1949 until 1955, before being reissued by the Gibson Custom Shop. "The ES-5 combines the acclaimed features of the L-5 with the finest method of electronic guitar amplification. Three separately controlled, adjustable pickups reproduce the full, rich tones and harmonics to make the ES-5 truly 'the instrument of a thousand voices.'" -- Gibson catalog, circa 1951.

100% original, no modifications, original case (still has plastic on combination lock), Neck feels great, Beautiful flamed Maple woods. Frets in great shape. Professionally set up and maintained. Current strings Thomastic Infeld Bebop 11's 
Ready to gig.

description:
Here's something you don't see every day. If you're a Mike Campbell fan, or have lusted after an early 1950s Broadcaster or Nocaster but haven't won the lottery yet, this meticulous Fender Broadcaster reproduction by luthier John Scott of Nashville's Bluesman Vintage, is your answer.

This is the best Telecaster I have ever played. It is super resonant when played unplugged; literally vibrates your chest. Just amazing. This is an awesome Bluesman Vintage T-style modeled after Mike Campbell's 1950's Broadcaster. 

The guitar is very lightweight, in the low 6 lbs range, and really rings. Killer grain on the well-distressed swamp ash body. Compound radius 7.25-9.5 birds eye maple neck. 6150 frets. Glendale bridge and saddles. And last, but certainly not least, Nunley Custom Pickups wound just like Mr. Campbell's Rock machine. If you love killer tone, you will love this!

This is as close as you are going to get to a '50s Broadcaster without shelling out $9,000 to $10,000 on the Mike Campbell Custom Shop Nocaster (only 25 made, good luck) or ponying up $35K for a real one.

Neck Width: at nut 1.687", 12th 2.02", 21st 2.19"
Neck Thickness: .975" at nut, 1.00" at 12th
Neck Carve: Nice and full C, if not U shaped.
Comes with a nice lightweight, rigid frame rectangular cordura plush case.
title: REDUCED. Bluesman Vintage '50s Fender Broadcaster Recreation

description:
Pedal works well, I just don't use it anymore. Works only with Roland GK pickups and cables. NO CABLES INCLUDED. Tons of fun, the sitar patch is my fav. Leave you phone # in the response.

From the web:
Fat synth sounds and effects in a compact pedal for GK-equipped guitars
Provides 6 synth-type waves and effects--Saw Lead, Square, Ring Mod, Slow Gear, Sitar and Acoustic
11 chorus and delay effects, plus Color and Level knobs for further tweaking
Rugged, dual-pedal design with simple, knob-based controls
Cool Synth-Type Sounds

If you're looking for something different, or maybe you lust after those vintage guitar-synth sounds, the BOSS WP-20G Wave Processor is for you. With a choice of six different waveforms like Saw Lead, Square, Ring Mod, Slow Gear and more, all it takes is your GK-ready guitar to create a tonal powerhouse complete with old-school knobs.
Onboard Modulation and Delay Effects

In true vintage fashion, the WP-20G provides 11 different kinds of chorus and delay, which can be turned on and off using one of the two built-in pedals. These effects are great for modulation and doubling, while additional tonal control is provided by a Color knob. And with the WP-20G's Level knob, you can blend dry guitar with the effected sound to your liking.
title: Boss WP-20G GK Effect Wave Processor Pedal

description:
I'm selling my axe fx rig.
Fractal Axe Fx II Mk II in good condition. It has some rack rash but no dings or anything that effects the 10/10 functionality - $1500
Matrix GT-1500FXBD Good as new condition. The absolute most reliable power amp I've ever used, and it doesn't really color the sound, and I've compared it to other power amps and it gives the best sound, I genuinely don't understand exactly how it is this good. 1u and 3 channels of 500 watts each. There was a short point where I ran 2 separate guitars and a bass rig through this, and it handled all 3 without any signs of slowing. Easily my favorite brand of power amp. - $700
Rocktron Midi Mate I'll be honest I haven't been gentle with this, it's not in great condition and I've tried everything to get the residue from previous stickers off and I can't get it off. Maybe some goo-gone would work. It still works perfectly but it just isn't as pretty as it was new. I enjoyed using it, and glowing in the dark is such a useful feature. - $100

$2300 individually, I'd honestly rather sell it all together for $2000.

All the cables are included and there's actually a couple extras. I'm happy to answer any kind of questions regarding this, I can't recommend this kind of rig enough. Perfect for guitar, bass, live usage, home practice, amateur and professional recording. There isn't anything that I've been able to say it's bad at. I've run 2 guitars through the axe fx, a guitar and a bass through the axe fx, changing patches with different setups, I genuinely can't think of any issues with any of it. 

I'm located in Sheepshead Bay Brooklyn but I work an Manhattan and I could probably deliver this anywhere reasonable. I'm not open to shipping, considering the nature of these things. If you need a rack case, I could probably also sell a 6u rack case.
Feel free to call/text/email me (Steve) with absolutely any questions (Will it work as a sound card / interface? Yes. Can I track wet and dry tracks simultaneously without any extra hardware? Yes. Can the matrix handle 8ohms? It can handle any ohm situation you have.)
