description:
I am selling my Roland  Juno-Gi 61 Key Synth with the Roland Cube Monitor for $850.00.  The instrument has only been played a few times and never left the apartment.  It is an amazing synthesizer! I am also including the gig bag.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0zE4quvGKDE

A Killer Synth and Much More!
How would you like a killer live-performance synth that can perform double duty as a serious 8-track recorder? With Roland's JUNO-Gi, that's exactly what you get. Roland loaded the JUNO-Gi up over 1,300 sounds and the same sound-shaping powers you've come to expect from the JUNO series. But here's a new twist: the JUNO-Gi is endowed with a full-functioning 8-track recorder. USB connectivity lets you turn the JUNO-Gi into a complete interface solution when paired with your favorite DAW software.

When it comes to a synth, the number and type of sounds available is a top concern. Roland packed the JUNO-Gi with over 1,300 sounds covering a huge array of instruments and styles. And if you're a gigging musician, you'll dig the Live Sets. Layer up to four sounds by stacking or splitting tones and save them together as a Live Set. Plus, a Special Live Set section dives in deep to take full advantage of the JUNO-Gi sound engine, giving you the most advanced synth sounds possible!

But of course, a gigging keyboard is only worth its salt if it's easy to move. Not only is the JUNO-Gi a snap to schlep from gig to gig (it's very lightweight), but you can run it on batteries too! Imagine how easy it would be to take your battery-powered JUNO-Gi synth and a battery-powered BA-330 keyboard amp to the gig. And you could play just about anywhere. Throw out a tip jar and rock on the corner! Be ready in an instant for an impromptu coffee house gig. The world will be your oyster!

As if this wasn't enough reason to click "Add to Cart," the JUNO-Gi is also a full-functioning 8-track digital record (2-track simultaneous recording, 8-track playback). You've got guitar/mic/line inputs so you can record nearly anything, and a 32GB SDHC card (not included) can hold up to 192 hours of recording (that's a lot!). Of course, you've got full import/export support for transferring files to and from a computer and the same effects built into BOSS's GT series are onboard to handle spicing up your tracks.

When you combine the JUNO-Gi with the bundled Cakewalk Sonar LE 8.5 software, you have a complete digital audio workstation package for your PC. In addition, the MIDI Controller Mode lets you operate the JUNO-Gi as a MIDI master keyboard for controlling your DAW or external MIDI devices. The JUNO-Gi is a powerhouse of a synth, with everything else just being icing on the cake.

Roland JUNO-Gi 61-key Synthesizer Features at a Glance:
Keyboard 61 keys (with velocity)
Maximum Polyphony 128 voices
Parts - Live Set (4 layers) + 16 parts
Wave Memory 128 MB (16-bit linear equivalent)
Preset Memory Live Set: 1,379, Tone: 788 + 256 (GM2), Rhythm Set: 14 + 9 (GM2)
User Memory Live Set: 256, Favorite: 100
Effects Multi-Effects: 2 systems, 79 types, Chorus: 3 types, Reverb: 5 types (Digital Recorder Section)
Tracks Track: 8, V-Track: 64
8 V-Tracks per each Track with up to 2-track simultaneous recording and up to 8-track playback
Maximum Number of Songs 99
Memory Capacity - SD memory card: supports SDHC cards to a maximum of 32 GB
Sample Rate 44.1kHz
Nominal Input Level: Line Input jacks: -10 dBu; Guitar/Mic Input Jack: Guitar: -20 dBu; MIC: -40 dBu
Insert Effects: 3 banks (Guitar, Mic, Line). Mastering Tool Kit, Reverb (USB Memory Song Player Section)
File Format Audio File: WAV, AIFF, MP3
Standard MIDI File: format-0/1
Number Of Songs: 99 Songs
External Memory USB memory: Supports USB 2.0 Hi-Speed Flash Memory (Sold Separately)
Rhythm Pattern Preset: 371, User: 99, Song (Digital Recorder): 99
Arpeggiator - Preset: 128, User: 64
Chord Memory Preset: 17
Controllers - Pitch Bend/Modulation Lever, D Beam Controller, S1/S2 Buttons, Sound Modify Knob x 6
Display 240 x 64 dots graphic LCD (with backlit)
External Memory SD/SDHC Card
A stunning synth and a whole lot more - Roland's JUNO-Gi!

description:
1972 Ibanez Telecaster Bass Guitar Fender Copy Made in Japan at the Fujigen Gakki manufacturing Plant.
Ivory White with Maple Fingerboard.

RARE. These were direct copies of the Fenders, down to the mid-body pickup design and the color.
The tele versions are particularly hard to find these days as they were not as common as the Jazz and Precision copies made during these years. This one is in overall very good condition.

CONDITION: 
Overall, very nice condition for it's age. Does have obvious age wear though. The Ivory color on the body has darkened a bit over time. The front and back of the bass have light wear and scratches, (the flash from the digital camera sometimes brings out marks that are not visible to the naked eye), and the front and back also have some long finish cracks/checking running lengthwise as seen in the photos. The neck is a nice, straight, slender C shape that is comfortable to play, and the frets have very little wear and lots of life left in them. Truss rod turns with no issues. The tuners work well and hold tune. 

The case is a recent Zenison hard shell case that the bass fits in well.
I've described the guitar and it's condition accurately and the photos pretty much tell the story. It plays like a dream.
If you have any questions, feel free to ask.

$500 cash. No lowball offers please and you MUST provide your email address and phone number. I won't reply unless you do. I need to know I'm responding to a real person.

***I would consider a direct trade for a US made G and L SB-1 bass. Otherwise, cash only. Thanks
title: Vintage Ibanez Telecaster Bass Copy 1972 Ivory Made in Japan

description:
SEATTLE WEEKLY VOL 42 NO 21 DEATH OF CHRIS CORNELL SOUNDGARDEN RARE!
This publication is only in Seattle, you cant find this magazine anywhere else. I live in Kent WA. Its dated May 24th 2017

His Band Started It All
Soundgarden formed in 1984, well before the city's golden age of rock began, and before most other notable guitar-heavy acts were playing, with the noted exception of Green River (which would split into Mudhoney and two-fifths of Pearl Jam).

 In the band's infancy, Cornell sang from behind the drum kit, flanked by bassist Hiro Yamamato and guitarist Kim Thayil. A year later, the vocalist deferred percussion duties, and the move changed the dynamic--and the trajectory--of the band. Ironically, Cornell decided to focus on vocals after watching Matt Cameron

 drum for the band Feedback. As he recalled thinking in Mark Yarm's book Everybody Loves Our Town, "Oh, that's what a good drummer is supposed to play like. Maybe my talent lies elsewhere." His epiphany opened the door for Cameron to join the band in 1986--and proved to be quite an understatement.

ONLY $5 FOR S&H
title: SEATTLE WEEKLY VOL 42 NO 21 DEATH OF CHRIS CORNELL SOUNDGARDEN RARE!

description: This Silvertone model 1477 (aka Silhouette or Bobkat) is an awesome, super vibey guitar. Made in 1966.  It's in great shape, all original, but is missing an inlay at the 3rd fret. You can't feel it when playing, and would be a super easy repair if you wanted.  Comes with a hard case (that may or may not be original, though it seems like it.  The neck is very beefy (front to back depth is about 1").  It's lightweight, and the pickups are crazy good and powerful. Very little fret wear and it plays great. I have flatwounds on it for extra retro goodness. The tuners work fine. And the little wire you see going from the jack to the bridge is just for grounding, since in the original form, these guitars were ungrounded. The wire (actually a fragment of a high e string) is to remove if for some reason you want to.
title: Silvertone 1477 Silhouette Bobkat 1966 - silverfoil pickups, w case

description:
THE SPACE:

Looking for a band/drummer (or both) to fill the second sublet spot in my studio on a monthly rent basis for $215/month. I've had the 170 sqft space for 7 years now and it's great: soundproof, air conditioning, utilities included. Open 24/hrs, 7 days a week, free parking in building, close to 7 train, very secure. Elevator and dollies for gear. I use it primarily for practicing and occasionally rehearsing in the evenings, my other sublettor uses it primarily for practicing drums.

YOUR HOURS:

26 hours a week guaranteed (mostly daytime, with some evenings and weekend time as well). Extra time (i.e. early and late) open for booking between the three of us as needed via internet calendar. To spare you the math, it works out to about $1.90 an hour.

THE GEAR:

I have a set of Gretsch USA Custom drums you're welcome to use, plus a bass amp, multiple guitar amps, and a PA with a 16-channel mixer. My other sublettor also has a set of Gretsch USA Custom drums in case you want to go two kits. I would prefer you don't bring in too much additional gear since space may get too tight, but we can negotiate if that's important to you.

YOU: 

Reliable, timely, professional, and good at communication. You don't have to be a pro but I assume you will be considering a hobbyist probably doesn't need 26 hours a week--although if you're a hobbyist, that's great too. Just make sure you're the kind of person two professional musicians want to share all their gear with!
title: Rehearsal/Practice Space/Studio

description:
Hey Craigslist, 

I have a few item to sell, please read the below descriptions.

Please note all items are for local, in person, cash only exchanges. Please provide a phone number for a response, if the post is still up the items are still available.

I can meet in Brooklyn 11216 or Manhattan 10010. 

1) Yamaha CS 15 analog mono synthesizer with Kenton Pro Solo MK11 midi/cv setup $780 -----
 I'm only selling the CS as a package with the Kenton

----The CS-15 is a wonderful and hard to find with a great tone and versatility unlike others. Excellent physical and working condition. Look this one up it has a bunch of features over other "similar" models.  Audio in with control, two ADSRs, independent LP, BP and HP filter switches for both oscillators independent glide for both voices and each oscillator can be controlled independently via separate CV inputs so you can send it two separate sequences or separate the oscillators tot play two different notes at once, the control is like having two note polyphony or two synths in one. The CS-15 also has CV and trigger outs to control other gear. All the waves sound strong but I have to say the triangle wave especially is one of the best I've ever heard, and mixed with the bandpass filter you can get those very vocal / vowel sounding patches. The bass is definitely strong and the leads can get to that very smooth and bubbly place which is a signature of the CS series. The PW and PMW is also very noteworthy with separate knobs for both sections. There is LFO control on the VCO, VCF and VCA.  I actually hate to see this one go especially since they are hard to come by if I happen to change my mind...


2) Korg Poly 800 analog synth with Moog slayer modification $500

The Poly 800 is in excellent physical and working condition and comes with two* sets of presents, you get the factory patches and another great set from an old school synth website I can't remember. There are Modifications for filter, resonance, audio input and FM mod, this takes an already good synth to great levels. The main switch controls modulation to DCO1 & 2, noise or audio input 1 or 2. Filter mods for hands on control of Cutoff, RES and FM* with an additional switch for the filter slope between 12 or 24. Independent knobs for level control of audio Inputs 1 and 2. The onboard step sequencer is a great plus and everyone loves the 800's modulation joystick which can combine a mixture of VCF DCO and pitch modulation. This synth has a distinct character and really can make many unique sounds.


3) Vintage Panasonic RX - 5080 Boom Box ($140) Ghetto Blaster with Mic and RCA input and output for computer of phone. 

This one is a beach day classic or great around the apartment.  The connections on the back make it easy to hook up a computer or iPod/iphone, I can include the cord to do so. This is a perfect alternative to bluetooth speakers and looks a lot better in my opinion. The box is in great physical condition, tone knob for nice bass/treb control. This can definitely get LOUD if you want it to. Runs on simple AC adapter cord (included) or D batteries, portable! This unit also has an ambient setting. Its a pretty random feature but it does give a cool effect. The tape player has been unreliable, it will play but often eats tapes, so I usually don't use it. The radio (FM/AM) receiver works but the antenna has been broken (this is an easy fix and can be replaced with any secondhand piece)


4) DOD R - 845 spring reverb ($180) In great condition all around. Sounds great on acoustic and electronic instruments, and has 4 band EQ.

5) Electro Harmonix Knock Out Attack Equalizer (25) Good working condition

6) Modified Boss SD-1 Super Overdrive pedal ($80) This pedal has 4 switches that create a variety of effects. I am not a guitar player, but it has worked well with analog synthesizers and drum machines. 


7) Heavy Duty Road case - Modular Case Project $50

18.5x14" Bottom 6" deep Top 3"deep

This is a reinforced card case that originally was for transportation of a 8 thousand dollar Phase One Digital Camera Back. I was going to possibly use this as a case for a modular set up but have since abandoned the project. The case has key / lock access with three spare key, metal clips for straps on both sides, ruler feet on the bottom side and carrying handle. 

Thanks!

description:
Rare Klemt Echolette S40 SHOWSTAR in amazing condition.
This guitar amp was made in West Germany in the 60s. As used by the Beatles when they were in Hamburg.

The Showstar is a 2x el34 based amp, basically a Marshall jtm45. -with the tremolo circuit-- The tone is impossibly deep and rich, with huge, HUGE, vintage, beefy iron vibe. I really can't over-stress how great the tone is. 

The heart and soul is of course, that amazing, gritty, distorted tone as you begin to heat things up. You simply MUST(!) jumper the inputs! Things start to get really interesting at about 1/2 volume and keep getting better the more you turn it up, until you are in full-on, unsurpassed, pure, real golden era, mind-destroying, cascading distortion. I ADORE the "sag" and compression you get out of this old girl when things start to get toasty. Glorious. This amp has phenomenal, tight break-up and creamy, squishy, gritty overdrive. It is a real wall-of-sound smear of stunning German tube tone. The trem is very nice and mellow. A lot like the marshall sound, less so the fender. The ORIGINAL! ....... heaven!

Shipping will be calculated more precisely depending on your location.
Local pick up possible too.
title: Vintage Klemt Echolette S40 SHOWSTAR 60s

description:
Hi,

I am selling my digital piano for space and a possible move. It is a beautiful instrument with many features, as well as a stunning furniture item. 

I learned to play on this instrument and eventually became a Piano teacher myself (at Frank and Camille's piano shop in NYC), the instrument has a solid weighted action which helped improve my finger dexterity and made it easy to do fast scales and arpeggios. European Pianos such as Hamburg Steinway, Bosendorfer and Schimmel have similar key weight. The LCD shows the keys you play as notes on a staff both bass and treble clef, this helps ALOT in learning to ready sheet music as you can reference a key to what is written on the sheet instantly. 

It has a wide array of voices from Piano, Guitar, Brass, Strings, Voice and Drums. You can do split voice,change tuning, and transposing. You can also play any voice with an auto-accompaniment which provides bass, drums, and pad backing for your playing, it changes as you change chords to match the harmony. 

It has a large sound with 60W 4 speaker system (2 subs and 2 regular) , full responsive MIDI in/out (ive hooked it up to many DAWs and VSTi and it works flawlessly. It also has dual headphone and audio out. 

The outside cabinet is beautiful, it is a wood grain mahogany with a polished finish, always cleaned and no major scratches or chips. The pedals still have their covers. It is compact and has a small footprint, perfect for homes and apartments. 

If you would like to come see it feel free to call me at  show contact info

i also have the manual for the piano as well as bench and polish which is included

description:
Thirty years on from his first single as part of Les Chanceliers, "Pag" remains the dean of Quebec Rock. Two-disc set Pagliaro Hit Parade collects 28 catchy rockers captured between 1969 and 1988. Recording in both official languages for much of his career, his string of early-'70s English gems like "Loving You Ain't Easy," "Rainshowers," and "Some Sing, Some Dance" constitute some of the best Badfinger songs that Badfinger never recorded (unless you're a native of Quebec, in which case the sentence becomes Badfinger's "Day After Day" is the best Pagliaro song that Pagliaro never recorded). The French material tends to more gritty, traditional rock & roll, led by his biggest hit "J'Entends Frapper."

description:
Product Description
The Shure Beta 57A Dynamic Microphone is a precision-engineered dynamic microphone designed for professional live sound reinforcement and studio recording. A tight supercardioid pattern on the Beta 57A delivers high gain before feedback and maximum isolation from other sound sources, with minimum off-axis tone coloration. Shure Beta 57A Dynamic Microphone Features: Tailored frequency response provides drums, guitars, vocals, and horns with studio quality sound, Uniform supercardioid pattern for high gain-before-feedback and superior rejection of off-axis sound, Hardened steel mesh grille that facilitates use of proximity effect and resists wear and abuse, Neodymium magnet for high signal-to-noise ratio output, Advanced pneumatic shock mount system that minimizes transmission of mechanical noise and vibration, Frequency response: 50 to 16,000 Hz. Shure Beta 57A Suggested Applications: Guitar Amp, Bass Amp, Acoustic Guitar, Brass and Saxophone, Snare Drums, Rack and Floor Toms, Congas, Woodwinds, and Lead Vocals.
From the Manufacturer
Consistently excellent performance has made Beta microphones the choice of top performers worldwide. Renowned for their warmth, presence and sensitivity to fine detail, Beta cartridge configurations and carefully tailored response curves are as distinctive as the artists who prefer them. All models feature maximum isolation and minimum off-axis coloration.

The Shure Beta 57A® is a high output supercardioid dynamic microphone designed for professional sound reinforcement and project studio recording. It maintains a true supercardioid pattern throughout its frequency range. This insures high gain-before-feedback, maximum isolation from other sound sources, and minimum off--axis tone coloration.

Excellent for acoustic and electric instruments as well as for vocals, the extremely versatile Beta 57A dynamic microphone provides optimal warmth and presence. Typical applications include drums, guitar amplifiers, brass, woodwinds and vocals.

Features
Tailored frequency response provides drums, guitars, vocals, and horns with studio quality sound
Uniform supercardioid pattern for high gain-before-feedback and superior rejection of off--axis sound
Hardened steel mesh grille that facilitates use of proximity effect and resists wear and abuse
Neodymium magnet for high signal--to--noise ratio output
Minimally affected by varying load impedance
Advanced pneumatic shock mount system that minimizes transmission of mechanical noise and vibration

description:
Please Mention the name of this item in your reply or it will be disregarded as SPAM.

Hohner Brian May Steinberger $500


This is a very cool guitar, it's  a Hohner Steinberger copy, but rather than heavy epoxy resin, it's made of wood, specifically one solid piece of Hard Rock Maple for the neck-through design with small Pine wings for the body (not unlike the earliest Fender Broadcasters, Esquires and Telecasters !) .

What makes this guitar  really fun  is that it's been wired the same as Brian May's Red Special, each pickup has an on/off/phase switch and all three pickups are wired in series, exactly as Brian May did on his guitar..  The bridge pickup has a coil tap, too.

This simple arrangement was cleverly devised using only 3 switches, each with three positions: 

ON (in phase) / OFF / ON (out of phase)

This gives you the same pallate of colors as Brian May's famous axe..

This guitar  also shares a similar neck profile and tremolo design, too...!

Comes with gig bag and extra strings.
title: Hohner Brian May Steinberger

description:
Fantastic recording mic. In almost brand new condition. Great for vocals and instruments
Whether you're recording lead vocals, acoustic guitar, strings, percussion or any other source instruments, the sE X1's hand-crafted and hand-tuned large diaphragm, gold-sputtered capsule outperforms every mic in its price class! 
The capsule is the true heart of the X1
Since all of SE's capsules are custom-made in-house, they are able to coax the very highest levels of performance out of their microphones. Surrounding the all-important electronics is a sturdy metal chassis finished in acoustically-damping black paint, to minimize any resonant frequencies in the microphone body. The sE X1 is also equipped with a 10dB pad and a low-cut bass filter, providing essential tools for recording a variety of sources in any environment.

description:
This is a 1950 Harmony Broadway Serial Number 1078H594. It is date stamped "S-50-T" which identifies it as being manufactured in the Summer of 1950. It has a number of bumps and bruises one would expect from a guitar that is almost 70 years old. There are two surface only cracks on the front: the first crack is on the upper right bout ~1.25" from the binding and the second is right above the lower end of the left F hole. Again, these are surface only cracks and do not affect body integrity or sound. There is a series of scratches along one side of the neck starting 1" below the nut. These, too, are surface only and do not affect the integrity of the neck structure or playability. The neck is straight and warp-free; there is no buzzing on any string up and down the neck; action is close; the guitar stays in tune. The checkered front binding is beautiful; the rear binding is plain. The pickguard is missing. Replacements may be found on the web. Its imperfections notwithstanding, this is a beautiful guitar that plays well and had a full, rich sound. This comes with a padded gig bag.

If you are interested in this item, please send me a message that includes an offer. Messages that just ask if it is available will be ignored.

This item is for pick up in Astoria. I accept cash only at the time of pickup by the buyer. Do not ask me if I will accept PayPal, or a cashier's check, or bank check, or money order, etc. that will clear before a friend or moving company comes to pick up this item for you. All scammers will be reported.
title: 1950 Harmony Broadway

LIKE BRAND NEW...Excellent condition. Purchased from guitar center union square last summer. It has always been in my home studio. Never traveled. Cosmetics and functions are all intact. Comes with music stand and power plug. I am only getting rid of it because I want to purchase a midi keyboard of same size and unfortunately cannot fit 2 of the same size in my small apartment. I keep it covered to avoid dust when not in use. Smoke free apt floor. I absolutely adore this keyboard. Fully weighted keys and sounds you get from this 40lb beast are second to none. I really hate to part with it but what is my loss is your gain! Pickup only. Cash only.
title: Korg sv-1 73 stage vintage piano

description: N.S."Buck" Brundage, this unit was manufactured from 1990 to 1997 and it was a favourite of producer Max Norman -- yes, he who worked with Megadeth on Rust In Peace, Countdown To Extinction and Youthanasia, not to mention Ozzy Osbourne in the Randy Rhoads era. Back in the day, ART said: "Power Plant combines the finest elements and saturation curves of 12AX7s into 6L6 tubes giving the user the thickest, heaviest crunch of classic tube amps without diction and articulation of notes! The Power Plant is one of the most versatile studio and live sound production tools available. It has totally separate clean and overdrive channels, master volume control, a switchable effects loop, and a +20 dB output for a power amp feed (this output has a unique equalization and pre-emphasis circuit that reflects the curve of a guitar amplification section)."

description:
The Heil PR 40 microphone boasts the widest frequency range of any dynamic mic in the Heil PR series. The PR 40 incorporates Heil's sage-like understanding of phasing plug placement, along with the use of a very large (1″), low mass diaphragm, and custom magnet metals housed in a specially designed microphone body.

The PR 40 diaphragm is shock mounted such that it is completely de-coupled from the anodized Champagne matte-finished steel body. In addition to dual mesh screens, each made with different diameter screen apertures, there is an internal breath blast filter on the diaphragm element itself, providing superb response for the human voice across the entire vocal range, without "popping" noises. In fact, the PR 40 will provide flawless, smooth, flat response from 28 Hz all the way up to the 18k Hz, making this a great microphone for everything from vocals, to bass drums and tom drums, to guitar and bass cabinet mic'ing and more.

In short, the PR 40 is known by professionals as the "thoroughbred work-horse" of professional sound recording and reinforcement.

The PR 40 is available in champagne, gold plate, or chrome plate. With all PR 40 models you get an adjustable cast metal microphone holder in a padded Leatherette bag with molded foam insert.
title: PRO LINE Heil PR-40 STUDIO MICROPHONE

description:
This is a one-of-kind prototype of the Warwick Corvette RockBass. I purchased this from the long-time Warwick distributor, Dana B Goods. 

It varies from the production model they settled on in several ways. The most obvious is the color. It's red stain is much nicer and classier than the blue stained or gloss black versions that were originally offered. The body is made of two nicely matched pieces of alder rather than three poorly matched pieces. The pickups are the German passive MEC Silver single-coils which were not initially offered. They sound much better than the active MECs which had a harsh metallic sound and even with the treble turned down, you could never approach the classic Jazz Bass sound of these pickups with the dual passive tone controls. No batteries needed and less to go wrong. The pickup locations are more like that of a 70's Fender Jazz which contributes to the aggressive growl these are known for. The neck construction varies slightly as well. It's a 2-piece maple neck with a satin finish. If you've ever played a German-made version, you'll understand why the necks are often compared to baseball bats. Not so with this one as it is much more comfortable. You might also note that the RockBass logo on this is smaller than the production model. It uses the German one-piece cast bridge from the Streamer Standard. As this is a prototype model, there is no serial number engraved into the neck. It's much lighter and more comfortable than a bubinga Corvette. And because of the clear coat, it will stay looking nice where the bubinga and swamp ash models will quickly show wear. I've included a photo showing it next to a German swamp ash model.

It is in MINT condition with only a few hours of play on it. Zero fret wear, straight neck, nice low action. Shortly after buying this bass, which was my introduction to Warwick, I picked up a used swamp ash model which was already worn so I played that one and kept this, unplayed, in a gig bag. I love this bass but simply can't justify that luxury anymore. I actually like this more than my swamp ash model. The grain is much nicer, it's lighter and the neck is much more comfortable. It also has the added versatility of being able to set the tone of each pickup separately. The pickups are identical.

I will include a used Warwick Deluxe Gig Bag

If you are interested, I have available a black Warwick bridge as well as a new set of black Gotoh tuners and black knobs as I was planning on swapping all the hardware from chrome to black. 

It currently has Fender Flatwounds on but I will install a new set of LaBella roundwounds, your choice of steel or nickel.

SERIOUS ONLY. I'm not Guitar Center and have no time for tire-kickers.
title: Warwick Corvette Prototype RockBass

description: Up for sale is my Gibson Les Paul, one of only twenty-four guitars built by the Gibson Factory and one of the very first reissues of the 1958 les paul. Also, not all of these guitars had the intense curly maple flame top like this one does. Paul Stanley and Ace Frehley both own one of these guitars. Also, Joe Perry once played this guitar back in 1980. These guitars have been called The Holy Grail by an article in vintage guitar magazine, that is if you can actually find one for sale and too because only a handful of these guitars were made. Also, the only way to document the guitar is by the original bill of sale or the newsletter sent out which I still have when I purchased it in 1978 from Strings and Things in Memphis TN. The first guitar on the right in the picture of the newsletter is a picture of this guitar without the sunburst finish on it. Like is says under the picture second best might as well be last.The guitar is a great investment and will increase in value each year. So if you are looking for the best and interested in the guitar let me know and I will get back in touch with you.
title: Gibson Les Paul - Vintage 1978 Reissue

description: For sale here is a beautiful 1989 Paul Reed Smith Custom 24- the model that started it all. This is from their original factory where they were banging out less than 500 guitars a year I believe. I'm an arch top guy now and I haven't played this excellent condition guitar for some time now- I'm the original owner- and it's time to let someone else appreciate it. It plays like a dream, has silver hardware, a wide-thin neck, the 'sweet' switch, and very light wear for a guitar of this or any age- a rarity. Plenty of fret life left on this Brazilian rosewood fingerboard. 5 position pickup switch was replaced by PRS years ago, all original otherwise. Can go from Strat to Les Paul sound with a turn of the dial- the best of both worlds. For players only- no low-ballers, re-sellers, or trades please.

description:
Selling Great River ME-1NV Mic preamp in a very good condition, fully working with a few light scratches. One of the best pre-amps out there, from clean to vintage sounds.
Comes with rack ears.
Cash only!
Thank You!


The Great River ME-1NV features iron in the signal path for that big vintage sound. Its no-latency output monitoring provides a buffered sound feed to your DAW workstation. The ME-1NV's hi-Z input is ideal to shape the sound for bass, electric guitar, and sound modules. Dual metering provides visual monitoring of gain staging. The ultra-quiet noise floor delivers "stealth" performance for rich, textured vocal sounds. The Great River MP-2NV is a stereo version of the ME-1NV that will add an enhanced image to your recordings. The Great River ME-1NV also has a full +70dB of input gain so you can take that prized ribbon mic out of the cabinet for a rich, creamy sound with all the detail and no muddiness.
Here's the bottom line. The Great River ME-1NV is a golden channel priced for the project studio and equally at home in a world class facility. This preamp has the ability to enhance the sound of high-end mics as well as being able to make inexpensive mics sound better. Just place your trusty SM57 in front of your guitar amp and run it through the ME-1NV, and you'll hear what we mean.
Great River ME-1NV Features:
	•	XLR balanced in and out connections 
	•	1/4" -10dbV output for 'no-latency' DAW monitoring 
	•	hi-Z input on front panel 
	•	Adjustable gain in 5db steps to 60db 
	•	Output gain from -25 to +10db; maximum overall gain 70db 
	•	Frequency response: 20Hz to 75kHz 
	•	Input and output monitor meters on each channel 
	•	2 or 3 stages of single ended solid state amplifier gain blocks 
	•	Gold plated switching contacts 
	•	Front panel polarity, phantom power, input impedance, and output loading switches 
	•	High quality, custom wound Sowter transformers 
	•	Output transistor and transformer with heavy 70ma Class A bias 
	•	Local regulating of each channel 
	•	Long service life components 
	•	TRS insert patch ahead of the output amplifier 
	•	110, 220 volts, either 50 or 60Hz operation with external switching 
	•	2 year warranty with registration 
	•	Iron in the signal path for that 'Big Vintage Sound' 
	•	Zero-latency output monitoring provides a buffered sound feed to a DAW workstation 
	•	hi-Z input is ideal to shape the sound for bass, electric guitar, and sound modules 
	•	Dual metering provides visual monitoring of gain staging 
	•	Ultra quiet noise floor with 'stealth' performance for rich, textured vocal sounds
title: Great River ME-1NV Mic preamp

description:
The Comanche is G&L's flagship model, a design directly influenced by Leo Fender's entire life and work. This guitar has gone through 14 years of non-stop playing by a professional musician in Brooklyn, making it well seasoned, opening up the tonal qualities of the wood. There is truly something magical about this guitar in particular, from the highly figured wood to its tonal characteristics, having a glassy top end with still a very robust bottom. 
 It has some wear but the structure and playability was never affected, giving the instrument a true vintage vibe. The biggest blemish is on the lower bout (shown in pictures). The neck is tapered, starting slim near the nut and gradually going to a medium profile towards the bridge, giving the perfect medium from playing open chords to having the space needed for intricate solos in the upper register.  It has been professionally setup in the beginning of last year and the action/intonation has stayed put since. The pick guard, originally white, has turned over time into a lovely gold color, which you never see on Comanches. The instrument is balance and the body has been shaped so well, it really fits like a glove. 
 This guitar is versatile! It has 3 hum canceling Z-coil pickups and a mini toggle expander switch that engages multiple pickups at the same time, ranging from a true Stratocaster sound to a beefier Humbucker. Finishing touches feature locking tuners, a whammy bar (not shown), birds eye maple neck (finished with gun oil), and a swamp ash body. Any serious questions please feel free to message. Visit the G&L website for specs and write up.
title: G&L Comanche Made in USA Stratocaster

description:
Hi everyone, I have a great Fender electric guitar that was "custom" built / designed using American Design Experience - which is Fender's online function where you can pick out all the colors, features etc. of an American Stratocaster. This guitar is pretty much decked out with the best options on ADE:
-Maple neck with black dock inlays
-S-1 switching with a push button in the volume knob 
-Fender Modern Locking tuners
-Noiseless Fender N-3 SSS pickups
-American Elite Trem
-comes with locking TSA hardshell case 

Essentially the same idea as an American Elite, which is pretty awesome. Definitely a step above the standard american and deluxe american. This configuration cost $1,749.99 on the website and was built in 2014. 

Definitely has wear - tried to picture damage as best I could. Obviously has been played - this is not for someone who is bothered by that. It has a number of markings, lots of pick scratches (I've considered replacing the pickguard, but it never really bothered me enough to do so), some chips on the sides of the body, etc. 

I am not interested in any trades or offers, price is final. You won't get a better strat for a grand, and I don't need to get rid of it - I'd just as soon keep it if it doesn't sell here. I'm trying to downsize my collection a bit and this one is a bit too nice for my limited current needs.
title: American Fender Stratocaster

 MUST PROVIDE A TELE # OR NO RESPONSE WILL BE GIVEN - CASH ONLY, NO TRADES! NEW ONES GO FOR OVER $3K, SO MAKE A REAL OFFER ON THIS SWEET GUITAR!

 As a longtime Jackson endorser (since 1986) and lead guitarist for one of the world's biggest-selling rock bands, Def Leppard's Phil Collen has deftly wrung numerous classic riffs from Jackson guitars. It's impossible to imagine the '80s and '90s rock charts--or Jackson history--without him.

 Collen's PC1 Dinky was one of the original Jackson signature instruments, and continues to stand out in modern times with its staple exotic woods and a Jackson Sustainer/Driver. 

 The new USA Signature Phil Collen PC1 Satin Stain model boasts premium features including a caramelized mahogany body with 1/8" quilt maple top, bolt-on two-piece caramelized quartersawn flame maple neck with hand-rubbed urethane gel on the back and graphite reinforcement, 12-16 in. compound radius caramelized flame maple fingerboard with 24 jumbo frets, convenient thumbwheel truss rod butt adjust and licensed Fender Stratocaster headstock.

 Collen's favored H/S/S configuration is also here, with a DiMarzio DP-152-F bridge pickup, DiMarzio HS-2 DP116 middle pickup and a PC1 Sustainer Driver as the neck pickup. Equipped with master volume, master tone and intensity control knobs, as well as a five-way blade switch to tweak and refine tone, a Floyd Rose Original tremolo with die-cast tuners and satin gold hardware. Includes hardshell case.
title: JACKSON PC1 USA SIGNATURE PHIL COLLEN W/OHSC

description:
Carvin fretless AC 40    New condition,  great acoustic tone,  gold hardware,  traditional head stock,  active electronics

$450   (This is $200 below average Ebay sale)

description:
This is an impeccably built 1964 Fender Deluxe Reverb Clone down to every last detail. 

Make an offer and it could be yours!

BFDR Build by Stu-Daddy Amps of Warren, MI


It is a hand wired replica of a 1964 Fender Deluxe Reverb guitar amplifier, handwired by Stu Daddy. This amp is the finest replica you can buy, in my opinion. This amp provides a tweed tone stack (channel 1) and a stock deluxe reverb tone stack (channel 2) and will overdrive very nicely. This is the same setup that he handwired for Johnny Lang's deluxe reverb amps. Approximate output is 20W. The 1964 Blackface Deluxe Reverb circuit design is the AB763 with reverb circuit. 


This version of the circuit in this amp is slightly modded and does away with the double redundancy of 2 channel Blackface Fender amps. Of course these mods are undoable and the stock circuit is always available. 

This version turns channel 1 the normal channel into a tweed/brown tone stack and he also equally weights both the normal and vibrato channels. The result is the Normal channel is as loud as the Vibrato channel with a bit more darker top end but with much more fatter midrange voice and the first order harmonics are richer.

Keep in mind that the Vibrato channel is kept stock. This allows for more tonal variations. The vibrato channel has the traditional Fender blackface tone, but this amp has a remarkably tight bottom end in either channel. The traditional 'farting out' usually experienced is gone.

With single coils the distortion is very 'Fendery' with bite appearing w/ hard pick attack at volume 4 in either channel and becoming more saturated evenly as selected amp channel is turned up. At ~ 8 on normal and ~ 9 on vibrato channel, headroom has disappeared and amp is nearly saturated. With slightly overwound single coils the amp drives a bit more, and P90's / Humbuckers bring a strong grind to the table as you'd expect. Distortion is even-ordered and very musical in either channel.

The amp works best with an A-B box. 'A' the Vibrato channel for clean and sparkling rythyms or leads, 'B' the normal channel for crunch or a Marshall-esque leads.

Many tonal combinations are possible, and unless you just have to have it, you can leave your stomps at home. Amp is remarkably quiet! With the modifications made to this circuit this amp will allow the player to cover all the musical styles of Rock,Blues and Country music with vintage blackface flavor.

*Specifications*
Hand built circuit board with tinned eyelets for flawless solder joints.
Solid pine finger jointed cabinet provides the warm round tone.
Hand built cabinet and you will notice careful details like period correct roundovers that are unavailable with commercially built cabinets.
Heavy weight premium felt backed tolex exactly like Fender used to use.
Cabinet interior and grill cloth aged slightly for that vintage look.
The chassis is a mojotone and faceplate is period correct except that the amp is upgraded to 10' 3W 18AWG grounded power cord and fully functional grounded AC outlet.
Sozo vintage blue molded capacitors in the tone stacks and silver mica Tone caps.
All Sprague Atom eletrolytics.
Carbon comp resistors.
Carling switches.
Switchcraft jacks
Mojotone metal shaft pots
Solid core push back wiring
Belltone octal and preamp tube sockets
Accutronics reverb tank
Period correct reverb wires
Vintage correct two button footswitch included
Vintage Fender Deluxe Reverb transformers for that vintage tone.
Class AB fixed adjustable bias
Output is approx. 20W

All of the vintage tone and reliability of PTP wiring, with none of the 55 year old trouble.

Fenders New Custom Deluxe 65' PTP wired is $2,500 and does not have the quality of the components in this amp.

The workmanship is far beyond what Fender ever did.

No shortcuts on this build, top quality components through out. 
You just need to look at the pictures to know what you are buying. 

Comes with a D2F padded cover. This is absolutely in new mint condition.

Contact me for more Pictures 


Questions? Text or Call  show contact info
title: 1964 Fender Deluxe Reverb - AB763

description:
For sale is a Roland Cube Street EX in an excellent condition.  I am selling it since I am not using it anymore.  Everything is in a working condition.  It comes with power supply.  I am also including the original box that came with it.  See details below for more information.  If you have any questions, let me know.  Thanks!

OVERVIEW
Big stereo sound that you can take anywhere.

With its compact size and battery-powered operation, Roland's CUBE Street was a huge hit among traveling musicians. Now, the new CUBE Street EX infuses the popular mobile amp with a huge performance upgrade that delivers more projection, more channels and more versatility. It offers 50W of power and a stereo speaker system with dual 8" woofers, and 2" tweeters provide clean, punchy sound for larger crowds, while four independent channels offer abundant connections for a variety of mics and instruments. Detailed sound adjustment is available with separate EQ and reverb controls, and great guitar tones are dialed in easily with the onboard COSM amps. Selectable power modes provide up to 20 hours of operation with eight AA batteries, and two CUBE Street EX units can be linked together for more sound coverage if needed. And with i-CUBE LINK, you can even plug in your iPhone or iPad to play backing music and record your performances.

COSM Models
The CUBE Street EX makes it easy for guitarists to plug in and get pro sounds immediately. COSM tones for electric guitar include Lead, Crunch, and Clean, plus an Acoustic Simulator for extra versatility from a single axe. There's also an AC preamp optimized for acoustic/electric guitar and a convenient built-in tuner. Chorus/delay and reverb effects are available as well, and these can be turned on/off with optional footswitches while performing.

FEATURES
Power: 50W (25W & 25W stereo)
AC or battery-powered (5 hours at 50W; 10 hours at 25W; 20 hours at 10W)
Speakers: 2x8" woofers; 2x2" tweeters
Four independent channels for connecting a variety of mics, instruments, and audio devices
Two XLR mic inputs allow two vocalists to perform at once
COSM tones for electric guitar, including Clean, Crunch, and Lead; preamp for acoustic guitar provides clean, natural sound
Angled back for use as a stage monitor; mounting hole for use with optional ST-A95 Speaker Stand
Stereo Line Out jacks for connecting to an external sound system when used as a stage monitor
Stereo Link jacks to connect a second CUBE Street EX for broader sound coverage
Easy recording into your iPhone/iPad via i-CUBE LINK and free CUBE JAM app
Dimensions: 19.4" x 13.5" x 12.1"
Weight: 16.5 lb.
title: Roland Cube Street EX

description:
Rare/vintage (1986) Fast Forward Designs Midi Step Foot Pedals in very good condition.  Made in Japan by Hammond-Suzuki.  Original power supply is missing but I understand that you can use a standard 9VDC guitar stomp box power supply with a negative center pin.

Functions include add octave, hold and repeat. Modes include transpose, volume adjustment, repeat rate, set midi channels, midi functions like vibrato and sustain when using a keyboard.  Intuitive and easy to use with any keyboard that has a midi-in.  Just connect via midi to your synthesizer and you can play with your feet.  Has 13 note pedals, i.e. one octave. 

It does more than just play notes on your synthesizer: it can start and stop your sequencer or drum machine, start various delayed (modulation wheel) vibrato ramps, turn glide on and off, add octave doubling, hold notes, repeat notes, act as a sustain pedal, set the volume on your MIDI module, octave transpose, and transpose into different keys (pitch offset). These actions can all be controlled from your feet, with out having to stoop down to change settings!!

It also plays polyphonically, so when used with the "hold" feature, you can form chords and stacks!! Or, if you are sitting down, you can do a "two feet" bass pedal performance.

Happy to send more photos upon request...Cash only.
title: Fast Forward Designs Midi Step

description:
This wireless, 200 watt PA system is perfect for events, and you'll be the life of the party - you can move around with ease and still be heard on this surprisingly powerful amp. The 8' full range speaker projects your voice and audio with gusto, and a ported enclosure design adds extra punch to the bass. 

It comes with a wireless mic that operates at a distance up to 100 feet, as well as two wireless mic sets that can be clipped to your clothing (all three wireless microphones are battery-operated). The amp has a telescoping handle and castor wheels for easy portability. It runs on a rechargeable battery, so you don't need to keep buying new batteries - simply plug in and charge with the included AC adaptor. Four multi-color LEDs notify you when the power is on, when the unit is charging, when the battery is low, and when the wireless mic is operating. Adjust the sound to your liking with the treble and bass controls. This amp even includes an echo knob for a wicked sounding voice effect. The PWMA230 also has plenty of external inputs - four ¼' jack inputs total for two wired microphones, CD or MP3 player, guitar, and any other external audio device. Comes with a 10' audio cord, and a 6' outlet cord.

We used this only a handful of times so it is in great condition.

Sold on Pyle Pro for $371.99: https://www.pyleaudio.com/sku/PWMA230/200W-VHF-Wireless-Battery-Powered-PA-System. This item consistently gets raving reviews, with many rating it 5/5 stars!

Must pick up item M-F between 10 am - 5 pm. We are located on Broadway, just south of Wall Street.

description: I've got a classic vibe 60's strat that I bought last February as a bit of a project guitar, and haven't used it all that much. I swapped out the stock pick ups for a set of Seymour Duncan SSL-1 Vintage Staggered Single Coils. I also rewired the guitar completely with all American made parts (pots, wires, 5 way switch) and wired it so that there is a master volume, master tone and then a blender pot to blend the neck and bridge pick ups together. This guitar has beautiful cleans all around, ESPECIALLY on the neck pickup. I'm selling this with everything I mentioned, and will also throw in the original pick ups as well as the gig bag that I bought along with it. If you've ever played one of these then you know that they're surprisingly solid guitars. With the things I put into, you can't even tell that it's a squier!
title: Classic Vibe 60's Strat w/ Upgrades!

Do you want an amp that's pristine OR one that has battle scars and looks like it played many gigs.  If you want the pristine one - stop reading now.  If you want a Made in the USA (all the new ones are made in Mexico) vintage design then this one's for you.

I'm selling an 80's USA Built Fender Hot Rod Deville 410 as in 60 watts of power into four 10 inch speakers.  This amp rocks with a Clean and Distorted Channel plus a Spring Reverb - thats it. The electonics are MINT.  The amp was serviced last year.  All of the tubes, both input jacks and the Spring Reverb Tank was replaced.  All of the original Fender Eminence speakers are still there.

As you can see the tolex has battle scars and the speaker grille is worn but that's character from a long very well played life.  The controls have labels as most of the lettering has worn off.  The important thing is that behind that look you are getting electronics are excellent.

This amp also has removable wheels installed. The wheels just pull out of the sockets in the base.  I'm also including the original Fender Foot Pedal and a mint Fender cover.

TUBE CIRCUITRY
Simply put, there's really nothing quite like the pure, powerful sound of a Fender tube amplifier. For decades, the tonal richness and touch-sensitive dynamics of real tubes have given Fender amps a defining and unmistakable voice, as heard on most professional recordings and performances of the past 60 years--the music you've known your whole life.

SPRING REVERB - Not Electronic
Among their many fine sonic attributes, Fender guitar amps like this one are prized in particular for their luscious spring reverb. For that wet, shimmering ambient sound ranging from subtle to cavernous, Fender lets you dial it in exactly to taste.

EFFECTS LOOP
For perfect placement of your outboard effects in the signal chain, this amp features an effects loop with ¼" preamp output and power amp input jacks.
title: Fender Hot Rod Deville 410 - USA Built

description:
I have a BRAND NEW NEVER OPENED iRig Acoustic for Sale

The best-selling guitar interface goes acoustic.

iRig Acoustic is a revolutionary new microphone solution that easily connects your acoustic guitar to an iPhone, iPad, Android device or Mac with stunningly professional sound quality. 

The size of a large plectrum, iRig Acoustic easily clips inside the sound hole of any acoustic guitar, yet delivers sound quality that rivals complex, expensive recording setups for a fraction of the price. 

iRig Acoustic captures the full range and timbre of your instrument in the most life-like manner. Unlike magnetic or piezo solutions, iRig Acoustic doesn't color the sound of your instrument, and offers extended frequency response and low-noise circuitry throughout. 

The output of iRig Acoustic connects directly to your iPhone, iPad, Android device, or Mac, and offers a 1/8" headphone output for monitoring. No batteries or power is required, making it an incredibly simple, compact way to perform or record anywhere. 

iRig Acoustic is designed to connect to IK's new AmpliTube Acoustic app, packed with tons of killer effects and features designed for acoustic guitarists. It's also fully compliant with dozens of other top apps, from Apple's GarageBand to Samsung's SoundCamp. 

With a revolutionary design, aggressive price point and killer sound quality, iRig Acoustic lets acoustic players join the mobile music revolution.

FEATURES
Ultra-compact clip-on microphone for acoustic guitar
Connects directly to iOS, Android and Mac
Extended frequency response (15 Hkz - 20 kHz)
Fits nearly any acoustic instrument
Integrated headphone output
Includes travel case
.
.

Focusrite Scarlett 18i8 recording interface. From a clean, non-smoking home studio. Hate to part with it but need the money.
Comes in original box/packaging. Have used this to record two full-length albums. Very sturdy, reliable and has clear signal. Focusrite pre-amps sound great. The first two inputs offer Mic/Line/Instrument on universal XLR/TRS connectors, while inputs 3 and 4 offer Mic/Line capability on universal XLRs-all four are on the front panel with pads and 48V phantom power. An ADAT optical digital connector (Lightpipe) provides eight additional digital inputs that can also be used with external mic preamps, which I have also done.
-Four award-winning Focusrite mic pres 18 Separate Inputs, 8 Independent Outputs
-Two independent headphone outputs each with a level control
Rugged metal unibody chassis. High quality 24bit 96KHz audio interface for Mac, PC and iPad

-Housed in a compact red unibody metal case to withstand the rigors of the road-and the studio. Input level controls feature signal halos-LED rings around the level control that give a simple and immediate go/no-go level indication: green means there is a recordable signal while red indicates overload. description:
Ibanez Roadstar II PRO540 Radius (1987) Bright Blue Burst

This is a quite rare Ibanez model, almost vintage I would say: it's been released in 1987 so it turns 30 this year.The finish is of course worn out here and there due to extensive usage; nevertheless it still plays really well: it's been regularly set up through the years and two years ago I had the whole fretboard refretted by a luthier here in NYC with stainless steel jumbo frets. All parts are original with the bridge humbucker being the exception: the original DiMarzio has been swapped with a Seymour Duncan Invader.The guitar comes with a hard case.

P.S. The volume and tone knobs have been recently replaced with new ones, purchased from Ibanez online store; also the plastic backplate has been replaced with a new one.

Specs from Ibanez Wikia: http://ibanez.wikia.com/wiki/540R
More specs from Axebition: http://www.axebition.com/electric-guitar/ibanez-540r

Album Notes
Personnel: Lenny Kravitz (vocals, guitar, organ, bass, drums); Slash, Adam Widoff (guitar); Nancy Ives (cello); Karl Denson, Butch Tomas (saxophone); Mike Hunter (trumpet); Sean Ono Lennon (piano); Henry Hirsch (keyboards, bass); Lebron Scott (bass); Zoro (drums).On MAMA SAID, Lenny Kravitz builds on the edgy soul-rock of his debut, streamlining his sound in both songcraft and production. The opener, "Fields of Joy," moves from ethereal verses that evoke a bucolic summer's day to power-chord-heavy refrains and screaming guitar solos. The Stax/Volt-esque soul of "Stand By My Woman," the bossa nova groove of "What Goes Around Comes Around" (which finds Kravitz mining a clear Curtis Mayfield influence), and the heavily phased rocker "Stop Draggin' Around" are all finely honed tributes to classic '60s and '70s sounds.That Kravitz is an unabashed fan of the old school is what, ultimately, makes his music so enjoyable, and he manages to synthesize his influences with style and economy. MAMA SAID's two standout tracks, "Always on the Run" and "It Ain't Over 'Til It's Over," are cases in point. The former is a lean, riff-driven rock song that recalls both Jimi Hendrix and early Funkadelic; the latter a string-sweetened ballad that could have been pulled straight from the Philly Soul catalogue. Kravitz's flair for re-imagining rock, pop, and soul, topped by his fine production sense, keeps it all appealing. The buttons he pushes are no less pleasurable for being so familiar.

Personnel: Lenny Kravitz (vocals, guitar, organ, bass, drums); Slash, Adam Widoff (guitar); Nancy Ives (cello); Karl Denson, Butch Tomas (saxophone); Mike Hunter (trumpet); Sean Ono Lennon (piano); Henry Hirsch (keyboards, bass); Lebron Scott (bass); Zoro (drums).Personnel: Lenny Kravitz (vocals, guitar, sitar, Fender Rhodes piano, Mellotron, synthesizer, drums); Adam Widoff, Slash (guitar); Nancy Ives (cello); Butch Tomas, Karl Denson (saxophone); Michael Hunter (trumpet); The Phenix Horns, The Phoenix Horns (horns); Henry Hirsch (piano, organ, Mellotron, mini-Moog synthesizer); Sean Lennon (piano); David Domanich, Zoro (drums).Audio Mixer: Henry Hirsch.Photographer: James Calderarro.Arranger: Lenny Kravitz.On MAMA SAID, Lenny Kravitz builds on the edgy soul-rock of his debut, streamlining his sound in both songcraft and production. MAMA SAID's two standout tracks, "Always on the Run" and "It Ain't Over 'Til It's Over," are cases in point. The former is a lean, riff-driven rock song that recalls both Jimi Hendrix and early Funkadelic; the latter a string-sweetened ballad that could have been pulled straight from the Philly Soul catalogue. description:
One Serious Amplifier!   I have had this amp for years and is was only used about 20 or less times.

The Peavey Classic 50 212 tube combo amplifier lets you take your tone further. Three 12AX7 preamp tubes and four EL84 power tubes give you the power and headroom needed for everything from singing cleans to aggressive, over the top distortion. Kick on the sweet spring reverb, and you'll wonder where the Classic 50 212 has been all your life. You can't deny there's a ton of value packed into the Peavey Classic 50 212 tube combo amplifier.

Peavey Classic 50 212 Tube Combo Amplifier at a Glance:
Gigging musicians love this amplifier
Real spring reverb for classic guitar tones
A quality amp by Peavey
Gigging musicians love this amplifier
The 50-watt, 2 x 12" Peavey Classic 50 212 is ready to gig as hard as you do. For most medium- to large-sized venues, 50 watts is all you need to be heard once you're miked up. Footswitchable channels (footswitch included) give you a wide tonal range to play with, and a speaker output for an extension cab makes it easy to expand your rig. It can be hard to find a combo amplifier that's adept at many musical styles while still being practical for the average musician, but the Peavey Classic 50 212 nails it.

Real spring reverb for classic guitar tones
On the Classic 50 212, you'll find a genuine spring reverb, giving you access to iconic guitar tones. Even if you don't play surf rock, you'll find this combo amp's reverb to be a cut above the stock reverb found in most amplifiers in this class. And the reverb is even switchable with the included footswitch.

A quality amp by Peavey
Peavey has been making innovative electronics for musicians since 1965. Found on professional stages around the world, you can count on your Peavey Classic 50 212 combo amplifier.

Peavey Classic 50 212 Tube Combo Amplifier Features:
2-channel tube combo amplifier with 2 x 12" speakers
50W is an ideal power rating for medium- to large-sized gigs
Footswitchable channels and spring reverb (footswitch included)
3 x 12AX7 preamp tubes and 4 x EL84 power tubes let you cover a lot of tonal range
Perfect for rock, blues, and country
Additional output for extension speaker cabinet
Get a truly gig-ready combo amp with the Peavey Classic 50 212!

description:
Hello!

I'm selling a pair of Shure KSM-141 microphones. I'm a professional classical musician and have used them to record about a dozen of my own concerts and to make a few audition recordings; but I haven't been using them recently. They are great microphones, very sensitive, well-respected by musicians and sound engineers, and will hopefully be put to good use again soon. They're also in very good condition - just a few small scratch marks on the surface of one of them (that I have shown in one of the pictures). These things are very durable and work perfectly!

I still have the carrying case, stereo microphone adapter, sponges, and paper manual. Also, I'd be happy to throw in a pair of mic stands (not pictured), though one is missing the end piece. (I will also be selling my Metric Halo ULN-2 Audio Interface soon, seperately.)

Please contact me for any questions or if you'd like to meet up to buy these (2) microphones (with included accessories)! 

In the meantime, here's some info about the Shur KSM-141 from Shure's website:

The KSM141 is a dual-pattern end-addressed condenser microphone with a rotating collar, allowing easy switching between a consistent cardioid or true omnidirectional polar pattern for smooth and extremely focused sound reproduction.

Designed for studio use, yet rugged enough for live applications, the KSM141 can withstand extremely high sound pressure levels (SPL). Its low self-noise and extended frequency response make it ideal for recording musical instruments.

FEATURES:

A mechanical polar pattern switch for highly consistent cardioid and true omnidirectional polar patterns. Provides flexibility in a wide variety of recording applications
Ultra-thin, 2.5 micron, 24 karat gold-layered, low mass Mylar® diaphragm for superior transient response
Class A, discrete, transformerless preamplifier for transparency, extremely fast transient response, no crossover distortion, and minimal harmonic and intermodulation distortion
Premium electronic components, including gold-plated internal and external connectors
Subsonic filter eliminates low frequency rumble (less than 17 Hz) caused by mechanical vibration
Three-position switchable pad (0 dB, 15 dB, and 25 dB) for handling extremely high sound pressure levels (SPLs)
Three-position switchable low-frequency filter to reduce background noise and counteract proximity effect

PERFORMANCE CHARACTERISTICS

Extended frequency response
Low self-noise
Exceptional reproduction of low-frequency sounds
Can withstand high sound pressure levels (SPL)
High output level
No crossover distortion
Uniform polar response
Superior common mode rejection and suppression of radio frequency interference

APPLICATIONS

Some typical applications for the KSM141 are listed below. Microphone use, however, is a matter of personal taste. The KSM141 may be used for a variety of applications other than those listed.

Acoustic instruments -- such as piano, guitar, drums, percussion, strings
Wind instruments -- brass and woodwind
Low frequency instruments -- such as double bass, electric bass, kick drum
Overhead miking -- drums or percussion
Ensembles -- choral or orchestral
Room ambiance pick-up -- guitar amplifier or drums
title: Great, Sensitive Microphones - (2) Shure KSM-141
